{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775907961087,"sessionID":"ses_283a356fcffemyg6eo3tM4HwaT","part":{"id":"prt_d7c5cf46b0016nnsTR1SAS07vr","messageID":"msg_d7c5cecfe00137P0pAjR810x27","sessionID":"ses_283a356fcffemyg6eo3tM4HwaT","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/python-sdk/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/python-sdk/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-027 Design: AgentCube Python SDK — CodeInterpreterClient\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-027  \n6: **Module:** `sdk-python`  \n7: **Language:** Python  \n8: **Size:** M (Medium)\n9: \n10: The AgentCube Python SDK provides a client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n11: \n12: This implementation integrates with:\n13: - **Workload Manager API**: Control plane for session lifecycle management\n14: - **Router API**: Data plane for code execution and file operations\n15: - **Agent Runtime API**: For agent workload invocation\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## Architecture\n20: \n21: ### High-Level Design\n22: \n23: ```\n24: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n25: │                         User Application (Python)                            │\n26: │                                                                              │\n27: │  ┌─────────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────────┐                 │\n28: │  │ CodeInterpreterClient   │    │  AgentRuntimeClient     │                 │\n29: │  │ ┌───────────────────┐   │    │ ┌───────────────────┐   │                 │\n30: │  │ │ Context Manager   │   │    │ │ Context Manager   │   │                 │\n31: │  │ │ Lifecycle Mgmt    │   │    │ │ Lifecycle Mgmt    │   │                 │\n32: │  │ └───────────────────┘   │    │ └───────────────────┘   │                 │\n33: │  └───────────┬─────────────┘    └───────────┬─────────────┘                 │\n34: │              │                              │                                │\n35: └──────────────┼──────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────┘\n36:                │                              │\n37:                ▼                              ▼\n38: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n39: │                         SDK Internal Layer                                   │\n40: │                                                                              │\n41: │  ┌─────────────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n42: │  │   ControlPlaneClient        │    │       Data Plane Clients            │  │\n43: │  │  ┌───────────────────────┐  │    │  ┌───────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n44: │  │  │ Session Management    │  │    │  │ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient│  │  │\n45: │  │  │ · create_session()    │──┘    │  │ · execute_command()           │  │  │\n46: │  │  │ · delete_session()    │       │  │ · run_code()                  │  │  │\n47: │  │  └───────────────────────┘       │  │ · write_file()                │  │  │\n48: │  │  HTTP Session (requests)         │  │ · upload_file()               │  │  │\n49: │  │  · Connection pooling            │  │ · download_file()             │  │  │\n50: │  │  · Auth: Bearer token            │  │ · list_files()                │  │  │\n51: │  └──────────────────────────────────┘  └───────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n52: │                                        ┌───────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n53: │                                        │ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient   │  │  │\n54: │                                        │ · bootstrap_session_id()      │  │  │\n55: │                                        │ · invoke()                    │  │  │\n56: │                                        └───────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n57: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n58:                │                              │\n59:                ▼                              ▼\n60: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n61: │                         External Services                                    │\n62: │                                                                              │\n63: │  ┌─────────────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n64: │  │   Workload Manager          │    │         Router                      │  │\n65: │  │  ┌───────────────────────┐  │    │  ┌───────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n66: │  │  │ POST /v1/code-        │  │    │  │ Code Interpreter Endpoints    │  │  │\n67: │  │  │         interpreter   │  │    │  │ · POST api/execute            │  │  │\n68: │  │  │ DELETE /v1/code-      │  │    │  │ · POST api/files              │  │  │\n69: │  │  │   interpreter/        │  │    │  │ · GET api/files/{path}        │  │  │\n70: │  │  │   sessions/{id}       │  │    │  └───────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n71: │  │  └───────────────────────┘  │    │  ┌───────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n72: │  │  Authorization: Bearer      │    │  │ Agent Runtime Endpoints       │  │  │\n73: │  └─────────────────────────────┘    │  │ · GET /invocations/           │  │  │\n74: │                                     │  │ · POST /invocations/          │  │  │\n75: │                                     │  └───────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n76: │                                     └─────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n77: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n78: ```\n79: \n80: ### Component Architecture\n81: \n82: ```\n83: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n84: │                     CodeInterpreterClient Flow                               │\n85: │                                                                              │\n86: │  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n87: │  │  User    │──▶│ __init__ │──▶│  router_ │──▶│ Control  │──▶│  Create  │  │\n88: │  │ Creates  │   │ Validate │   │  url     │   │  Plane   │   │  Session │  │\n89: │  │  Client  │   │  Config  │   │  check   │   │  Client  │   │   or     │  │\n90: │  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   │  Reuse   │  │\n91: │                                                              └────┬─────┘  │\n92: │                                                                   │        │\n93: │                              ┌────────────────────────────────────┘        │\n94: │                              │                                             │\n95: │                              ▼                                             │\n96: │  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n97: │  │  stop()  │◀──│ __exit__ │◀──│  Context │◀──│ DataPlane│◀──│ _init_   │  │\n98: │  │  Cleanup │   │ Cleanup  │   │  Manager │   │  Client  │   │data_plane│  │\n99: │  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘  │\n100: │       │                                                           │        │\n101: │       ▼                                                           ▼        │\n102: │  ┌──────────┐                                            ┌──────────────┐  │\n103: │  │  Close   │                                            │ Execute/Files│  │\n104: │  │  Session │                                            │ Operations   │  │\n105: │  └──────────┘                                            └──────────────┘  │\n106: │                                                                              │\n107: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n108: ```\n109: \n110: ### AgentRuntimeClient Architecture\n111: \n112: ```\n113: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n114: │                      AgentRuntimeClient Flow                                 │\n115: │                                                                              │\n116: │  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n117: │  │  User    │──▶│ __init__ │──▶│ router_  │──▶│ DataPlane│──▶│ Bootstrap│  │\n118: │  │ Creates  │   │ Validate │   │ url check│   │  Client  │   │ Session  │  │\n119: │  │  Client  │   │  Config  │   │          │   │          │   │   ID     │  │\n120: │  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └────┬─────┘  │\n121: │                                                                   │        │\n122: │                              ┌────────────────────────────────────┘        │\n123: │                              │                                             │\n124: │                              ▼                                             │\n125: │  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n126: │  │  close() │◀──│ __exit__ │◀──│  Context │◀──│  invoke()│◀──│  User    │  │\n127: │  │  Cleanup │   │ Cleanup  │   │  Manager │   │ POST JSON│   │ Invokes  │  │\n128: │  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   │ + Headers│   │  Agent   │  │\n129: │                                               └──────────┘   └──────────┘  │\n130: │                                                                              │\n131: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n132: ```\n133: \n134: ### Component Interactions\n135: \n136: | Component | Purpose | Input | Output |\n137: |-----------|---------|-------|--------|\n138: | **CodeInterpreterClient** | High-level client for code interpreter sessions | Configuration params | Session management, code execution |\n139: | **AgentRuntimeClient** | High-level client for agent runtime invocation | Agent name, namespace, payload | Invocation response |\n140: | **ControlPlaneClient** | Workload Manager API client | Session parameters | Session ID, deletion status |\n141: | **CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient** | Router API client for code operations | Commands, files, paths | Execution results, file data |\n142: | **AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient** | Router API client for agent invocation | Payload, session ID | HTTP response |\n143: | **create_session** | HTTP session factory | Pool config | requests.Session with adapter |\n144: | **read_token_from_file** | Service account token reader | File path | Token string or empty |\n145: | **get_logger** | Logging utility | Name, level | Logger instance |\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: ## Directory Structure\n150: \n151: ```\n152: sdk-python/\n153: ├── pyproject.toml                          # Package configuration\n154: ├── agentcube/\n155: │   ├── __init__.py                         # Public exports\n156: │   ├── code_interpreter.py                 # CodeInterpreterClient\n157: │   ├── agent_runtime.py                    # AgentRuntimeClient\n158: │   ├── exceptions.py                       # Exception hierarchy\n159: │   ├── clients/\n160: │   │   ├── __init__.py                     # Client re-exports\n161: │   │   ├── control_plane.py                # ControlPlaneClient\n162: │   │   ├── code_interpreter_data_plane.py  # CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n163: │   │   └── agent_runtime_data_plane.py     # AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n164: │   └── utils/\n165: │       ├── __init__.py                     # Module marker\n166: │       ├── http.py                         # create_session\n167: │       ├── utils.py                        # read_token_from_file\n168: │       └── log.py                          # get_logger\n169: ├── examples/\n170: │   ├── basic_usage.py                      # CodeInterpreter example\n171: │   └── agent_runtime_usage.py              # AgentRuntime example\n172: ├── scripts/\n173: │   └── e2e_picod_test.py                   # End-to-end test\n174: └── tests/\n175:     └── *.py                                # Unit tests\n176: ```\n177: \n178: ---\n179: \n180: ## Data Structures\n181: \n182: ### CodeInterpreterClient\n183: \n184: ```python\n185: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n186:     \"\"\"High-level client for Code Interpreter session management and execution.\n187:     \n188:     Fields (set in __init__):\n189:         name: str                    # Session name (default: \"my-interpreter\")\n190:         namespace: str               # Kubernetes namespace (default: \"default\")\n191:         ttl: int                     # Session TTL in seconds (default: 3600)\n192:         verbose: bool                # Enable verbose logging (default: False)\n193:         logger: logging.Logger       # Logger instance\n194:         cp_client: ControlPlaneClient  # Control plane client\n195:         router_url: str              # Router URL (required)\n196:         session_id: Optional[str]    # Session ID (created or provided)\n197:         dp_client: Optional[CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient]  # Data plane client\n198:     \"\"\"\n199: ```\n200: \n201: **Constructor Parameters:**\n202: \n203: | Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n204: |-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n205: | `name` | `str` | `\"my-interpreter\"` | Name for the code interpreter session |\n206: | `namespace` | `str` | `\"default\"` | Kubernetes namespace |\n207: | `ttl` | `int` | `3600` | Session TTL in seconds |\n208: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Workload Manager URL (or env `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`) |\n209: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Router URL (or env `ROUTER_URL`, required) |\n210: | `auth_token` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Auth token (or service account token file) |\n211: | `verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable verbose logging |\n212: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Existing session ID to reuse |\n213: \n214: ### AgentRuntimeClient\n215: \n216: ```python\n217: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n218:     \"\"\"High-level client for Agent Runtime invocation.\n219:     \n220:     Fields (set in __init__):\n221:         agent_name: str              # Agent name\n222:         namespace: str               # Kubernetes namespace (default: \"default\")\n223:         timeout: int                 # Read timeout (default: 120)\n224:         connect_timeout: float       # Connect timeout (default: 5.0)\n225:         logger: logging.Logger       # Logger instance\n226:         router_url: str              # Router URL (from arg or ROUTER_URL env)\n227:         session_id: Optional[str]    # Session ID (bootstrapped or provided)\n228:         dp_client: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient  # Data plane client\n229:     \"\"\"\n230: ```\n231: \n232: **Constructor Parameters:**\n233: \n234: | Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n235: |-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n236: | `agent_name` | `str` | (required) | Name of the agent to invoke |\n237: | `namespace` | `str` | `\"default\"` | Kubernetes namespace |\n238: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Router URL (or env `ROUTER_URL`) |\n239: | `verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable verbose logging |\n240: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Existing session ID to reuse |\n241: | `timeout` | `int` | `120` | Read timeout in seconds |\n242: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | `5.0` | Connect timeout in seconds |\n243: \n244: ### ControlPlaneClient\n245: \n246: ```python\n247: class ControlPlaneClient:\n248:     \"\"\"Control plane client for Workload Manager API.\n249:     \n250:     Fields:\n251:         base_url: str                # Workload Manager base URL\n252:         timeout: int                 # Read timeout (default: 120)\n253:         connect_timeout: float       # Connect timeout (default: 5.0)\n254:         session: requests.Session    # HTTP session with pooling\n255:     \"\"\"\n256: ```\n257: \n258: ### CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n259: \n260: ```python\n261: class CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n262:     \"\"\"Data plane client for Code Interpreter operations.\n263:     \n264:     Fields:\n265:         session_id: str              # Session ID for header\n266:         base_url: str                # Data plane base URL\n267:         timeout: int                 # Read timeout (default: 120)\n268:         connect_timeout: float       # Connect timeout (default: 5.0)\n269:         session: requests.Session    # HTTP session with pooling\n270:     \"\"\"\n271: ```\n272: \n273: ### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n274: \n275: ```python\n276: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n277:     \"\"\"Data plane client for Agent Runtime invocation.\n278:     \n279:     Constants:\n280:         SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n281:     \n282:     Fields:\n283:         base_url: str                # Data plane base URL\n284:         timeout: int                 # Read timeout (default: 120)\n285:         connect_timeout: float       # Connect timeout (default: 5.0)\n286:         session: requests.Session    # HTTP session with pooling\n287:     \"\"\"\n288: ```\n289: \n290: ---\n291: \n292: ## API Contracts\n293: \n294: ### Control Plane (Workload Manager)\n295: \n296: #### Session Creation\n297: \n298: ```\n299: POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter\n300: ```\n301: \n302: **Request:**\n303: ```json\n304: {\n305:   \"name\": \"my-interpreter\",\n306:   \"namespace\": \"default\",\n307:   \"ttl\": 3600,\n308:   \"metadata\": {}\n309: }\n310: ```\n311: \n312: **Response:**\n313: ```json\n314: {\n315:   \"sessionId\": \"abc-123-def\"\n316: }\n317: ```\n318: \n319: **Headers:**\n320: - `Content-Type: application/json`\n321: - `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token non-empty)\n322: \n323: **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n324: \n325: #### Session Deletion\n326: \n327: ```\n328: DELETE {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}\n329: ```\n330: \n331: **Behavior:**\n332: - Returns `True` on success (2xx)\n333: - Returns `True` on 404 (already deleted)\n334: - Returns `False` on other errors (logs warning)\n335: \n336: ### Data Plane (Code Interpreter)\n337: \n338: #### Base URL Construction\n339: \n340: ```python\n341: if base_url is not provided:\n342:     base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\n343:     self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n344: ```\n345: \n346: #### Execute Command\n347: \n348: ```\n349: POST {base_url}api/execute\n350: ```\n351: \n352: **Request:**\n353: ```json\n354: {\n355:   \"command\": [\"python3\", \"script.py\"],\n356:   \"timeout\": \"60s\"\n357: }\n358: ```\n359: \n360: **Response:**\n361: ```json\n362: {\n363:   \"stdout\": \"output text\",\n364:   \"stderr\": \"error text\",\n365:   \"exit_code\": 0\n366: }\n367: ```\n368: \n369: **Timeout Behavior:**\n370: - Read timeout: `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124)\n371: \n372: **Error Handling:**\n373: - Raises `CommandExecutionError` if `exit_code != 0`\n374: \n375: #### Write File\n376: \n377: ```\n378: POST {base_url}api/files\n379: ```\n380: \n381: **Request:**\n382: ```json\n383: {\n384:   \"path\": \"/workspace/script.py\",\n385:   \"content\": \"base64_encoded_content\",\n386:   \"mode\": \"0644\"\n387: }\n388: ```\n389: \n390: #### Upload File (Multipart)\n391: \n392: ```\n393: POST {base_url}api/files\n394: Content-Type: multipart/form-data\n395: ```\n396: \n397: **Form Data:**\n398: - `file`: Binary file content\n399: - `path`: Remote path\n400: - `mode`: File permissions (e.g., \"0644\")\n401: \n402: **Headers:**\n403: - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (only header, no JSON Content-Type)\n404: \n405: #### Download File\n406: \n407: ```\n408: GET {base_url}api/files/{clean_path}\n409: ```\n410: \n411: Where `clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`\n412: \n413: **Response:** Binary file content (streamed)\n414: \n415: #### List Files\n416: \n417: ```\n418: GET {base_url}api/files?path={path}\n419: ```\n420: \n421: ### Data Plane (Agent Runtime)\n422: \n423: #### Base URL Construction\n424: \n425: ```python\n426: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n427: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n428: ```\n429: \n430: #### Bootstrap Session ID\n431: \n432: ```\n433: GET {base_url}\n434: ```\n435: \n436: **Response Headers:**\n437: - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (required)\n438: \n439: **Error:**\n440: - Raises `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")` if header missing\n441: \n442: #### Invoke Agent\n443: \n444: ```\n445: POST {base_url}\n446: ```\n447: \n448: **Headers:**\n449: - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n450: - `Content-Type: application/json`\n451: \n452: **Request Body:** JSON payload (dict)\n453: \n454: **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` tuple\n455: \n456: ---\n457: \n458: ## Error Handling\n459: \n460: ### Exception Hierarchy\n461: \n462: ```\n463: AgentCubeError (base)\n464: ├── CommandExecutionError\n465: ├── SessionError\n466: └── DataPlaneError\n467: ```\n468: \n469: ### Exception Definitions\n470: \n471: ```python\n472: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n473:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n474:     pass\n475: \n476: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n477:     \"\"\"Raised when remote command returns non-zero exit code.\"\"\"\n478:     \n479:     def __init__(self, exit_code: int, stderr: str, command: Optional[str] = None):\n480:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n481:         self.stderr = stderr\n482:         self.command = command\n483:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n484: \n485: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n486:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails.\n487:     \n488:     Defined for extension; core client modules primarily use ValueError\n489:     or requests exceptions for session-related errors.\n490:     \"\"\"\n491:     pass\n492: \n493: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n494:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail.\n495:     \n496:     Defined for extension; core client modules may raise ValueError\n497:     or requests exceptions for data plane errors.\n498:     \"\"\"\n499:     pass\n500: ```\n501: \n502: ### Error Scenarios\n503: \n504: | Scenario | Error Type | Message/Behavior |\n505: |----------|------------|------------------|\n506: | Router URL not provided | `ValueError` | \"Router URL must be provided\" |\n507: | Session creation fails | `ValueError` / logs | Missing `sessionId` in response |\n508: | Data plane init fails after session create | Warning log + cleanup | Deletes session, re-raises |\n509: | Command non-zero exit | `CommandExecutionError` | Includes exit_code, stderr, command |\n510: | Missing session header | `ValueError` | \"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\" |\n511: | Invoke without session | `ValueError` | \"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\" |\n512: | Session not found (404) | Handled gracefully | Returns `True` from `delete_session` |\n513: \n514: ### Context Manager Cleanup\n515: \n516: **CodeInterpreterClient:**\n517: ```python\n518: def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None:\n519:     \"\"\"Cleanup on context exit (success or exception).\"\"\"\n520:     self.stop()\n521: \n522: def stop(self) -> None:\n523:     \"\"\"Stop the client: close data plane, delete session, close control plane.\"\"\"\n524:     # 1. Close data plane client\n525:     # 2. Delete control plane session (if session_id was created)\n526:     # 3. Close control plane HTTP session\n527: ```\n528: \n529: **AgentRuntimeClient:**\n530: ```python\n531: def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None:\n532:     \"\"\"Cleanup on context exit.\"\"\"\n533:     self.close()\n534: \n535: def close(self) -> None:\n536:     \"\"\"Close the underlying requests.Session.\"\"\"\n537: ```\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## Configuration Resolution\n542: \n543: ### No Centralized Configuration Class\n544: \n545: The SDK uses distributed configuration resolution across components:\n546: \n547: | Component | Setting | Resolution Order |\n548: |-----------|---------|------------------|\n549: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` | `workload_manager_url` arg → `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env |\n550: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `auth_token` | `auth_token` arg → `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` file |\n551: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` | `router_url` arg → `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n552: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` | `router_url` arg → `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n553: \n554: ### Default Timeouts\n555: \n556: | Component | Connect Timeout | Read Timeout |\n557: |-----------|-----------------|--------------|\n558: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `5.0` seconds | `120` seconds |\n559: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `5.0` seconds | `120` seconds |\n560: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | `5.0` seconds | `120` seconds |\n561: \n562: ### HTTP Connection Pool\n563: \n564: ```python\n565: defaults = {\n566:     \"pool_connections\": 10,\n567:     \"pool_maxsize\": 10,\n568: }\n569: ```\n570: \n571: ---\n572: \n573: ## Testing Strategy\n574: \n575: ### Test Levels\n576: \n577: | Level | Scope | Focus |\n578: |-------|-------|-------|\n579: | **Unit** | Individual classes/methods | Logic, error paths, edge cases |\n580: | **Integration** | Client + Mock Server | HTTP contract verification |\n581: | **E2E** | Full stack (optional) | Real service connectivity |\n582: \n583: ### Unit Test Coverage\n584: \n585: #### CodeInterpreterClient Tests\n586: \n587: ```python\n588: # test_code_interpreter.py\n589: class TestCodeInterpreterClient:\n590:     def test_init_requires_router_url(self):\n591:         \"\"\"Router URL must be provided via arg or ROUTER_URL env.\"\"\"\n592:         \n593:     def test_init_creates_session_when_not_provided(self):\n594:         \"\"\"Should create session via ControlPlaneClient.\"\"\"\n595:         \n596:     def test_init_reuses_provided_session_id(self):\n597:         \"\"\"Should not create new session when session_id provided.\"\"\"\n598:         \n599:     def test_data_plane_init_failure_cleanup(self):\n600:         \"\"\"Should delete session if data plane init fails after create.\"\"\"\n601:         \n602:     def test_context_manager_cleanup(self):\n603:         \"\"\"Should call stop() on context exit.\"\"\"\n604:         \n605:     def test_execute_command_delegates_to_data_plane(self):\n606:         \"\"\"Should delegate to CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.\"\"\"\n607:         \n608:     def test_run_code_python_path(self):\n609:         \"\"\"Should write file and execute python3 for python/py/python3.\"\"\"\n610: ```\n611: \n612: #### AgentRuntimeClient Tests\n613: \n614: ```python\n615: # test_agent_runtime.py\n616: class TestAgentRuntimeClient:\n617:     def test_bootstrap_session_id_on_init(self):\n618:         \"\"\"Should GET base URL and extract session header.\"\"\"\n619:         \n620:     def test_bootstrap_missing_header_raises(self):\n621:         \"\"\"Should raise ValueError if session header missing.\"\"\"\n622:         \n623:     def test_invoke_without_session_raises(self):\n624:         \"\"\"Should raise ValueError if session_id is falsy.\"\"\"\n625:         \n626:     def test_invoke_posts_json_with_headers(self):\n627:         \"\"\"Should POST JSON with session header.\"\"\"\n628:         \n629:     def test_context_manager_closes_session(self):\n630:         \"\"\"Should close HTTP session on context exit.\"\"\"\n631: ```\n632: \n633: #### ControlPlaneClient Tests\n634: \n635: ```python\n636: # test_control_plane.py\n637: class TestControlPlaneClient:\n638:     def test_create_session_posts_json(self):\n639:         \"\"\"Should POST to /v1/code-interpreter with correct body.\"\"\"\n640:         \n641:     def test_create_session_returns_session_id(self):\n642:         \"\"\"Should return sessionId from response.\"\"\"\n643:         \n644:     def test_create_session_missing_session_id_raises(self):\n645:         \"\"\"Should raise ValueError if response missing sessionId.\"\"\"\n646:         \n647:     def test_delete_session_returns_true_on_success(self):\n648:         \"\"\"Should return True on 2xx.\"\"\"\n649:         \n650:     def test_delete_session_returns_true_on_404(self):\n651:         \"\"\"Should return True on 404 (already deleted).\"\"\"\n652:         \n653:     def test_delete_session_returns_false_on_error(self):\n654:         \"\"\"Should return False and log warning on other errors.\"\"\"\n655:         \n656:     def test_auth_from_service_account_token(self):\n657:         \"\"\"Should read token from SA file when auth_token not provided.\"\"\"\n658: ```\n659: \n660: #### Data Plane Client Tests\n661: \n662: ```python\n663: # test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py\n664: class TestCodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n665:     def test_base_url_construction(self):\n666:         \"\"\"Should construct base URL from router_url + namespace + cr_name.\"\"\"\n667:         \n668:     def test_execute_command_posts_json(self):\n669:         \"\"\"Should POST to api/execute with command array and timeout.\"\"\"\n670:         \n671:     def test_execute_command_timeout_buffer(self):\n672:         \"\"\"Read timeout should be timeout + 2.0 seconds.\"\"\"\n673:         \n674:     def test_execute_command_raises_on_nonzero_exit(self):\n675:         \"\"\"Should raise CommandExecutionError on non-zero exit_code.\"\"\"\n676:         \n677:     def test_write_file_posts_base64(self):\n678:         \"\"\"Should POST to api/files with base64 content, path, mode.\"\"\"\n679:         \n680:     def test_upload_file_multipart(self):\n681:         \"\"\"Should POST multipart with file, path, mode, session header.\"\"\"\n682:         \n683:     def test_download_file_streams(self):\n684:         \"\"\"Should GET with stream=True for file download.\"\"\"\n685:         \n686:     def test_list_files_gets_with_path_query(self):\n687:         \"\"\"Should GET api/files with path query param.\"\"\"\n688: ```\n689: \n690: ### Mock Server Integration Tests\n691: \n692: ```python\n693: # Integration test example\n694: @pytest.fixture\n695: def mock_router():\n696:     \"\"\"Start mock Router server for testing.\"\"\"\n697:     # Using responses or httpserver library\n698:     \n699: def test_full_lifecycle(mock_router):\n700:     \"\"\"Test create session, execute, stop flow.\"\"\"\n701:     with CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=mock_router.url) as client:\n702:         result = client.execute_command(\"echo hello\")\n703:         assert result == \"hello\\n\"\n704:     # Verify session deleted on exit\n705: ```\n706: \n707: ### E2E Test Script\n708: \n709: ```python\n710: # scripts/e2e_picod_test.py\n711: \"\"\"End-to-end test for PicoD integration.\n712: \n713: Requires:\n714:     - Running Workload Manager\n715:     - Running Router\n716:     - Accessible Code Interpreter environment\n717: \n718: Usage:\n719:     python scripts/e2e_picod_test.py\n720: \"\"\"\n721: ```\n722: \n723: ---\n724: \n725: ## Dependencies\n726: \n727: ### Required\n728: \n729: ```toml\n730: [project]\n731: name = \"agentcube-sdk\"\n732: requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n733: dependencies = [\n734:     \"requests\",\n735:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n736:     \"cryptography\",\n737: ]\n738: \n739: [build-system]\n740: requires = [\"setuptools>=61.0\", \"wheel\"]\n741: build-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n742: ```\n743: \n744: ### Package Discovery\n745: \n746: ```toml\n747: [tool.setuptools.packages.find]\n748: where = [\".\"]\n749: include = [\"agentcube*\"]\n750: namespaces = false\n751: ```\n752: \n753: ---\n754: \n755: ## Public API Surface\n756: \n757: ### Root Exports (`agentcube/__init__.py`)\n758: \n759: ```python\n760: from .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n761: from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n762: \n763: __all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n764: ```\n765: \n766: ### Clients Subpackage (`agentcube/clients/__init__.py`)\n767: \n768: ```python\n769: __all__ = [\n770:     \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n771:     \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n772:     \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n773: ]\n774: ```\n775: \n776: ---\n777: \n778: ## Implementation Notes\n779: \n780: ### Session Header Management\n781: \n782: - Header name: `x-agentcube-session-id` (lowercase)\n783: - Set as default on data plane HTTP session\n784: - Explicitly set on multipart uploads\n785: \n786: ### Timeout Handling\n787: \n788: - Control plane: `(connect_timeout, timeout)` tuple\n789: - Data plane execute: `timeout + 2.0` buffer to prevent race with PicoD\n790: - Per-call override supported via method `timeout` parameter\n791: \n792: ### Python Code Execution Path\n793: \n794: When `run_code()` called with `language` in `(\"python\", \"py\", \"python3\")`:\n795: \n796: 1. Generate timestamped filename: `{name}_{timestamp}.py`\n797: 2. Write code via `write_file()`\n798: 3. Execute via `execute_command(f\"python3 {filename}\")`\n799: \n800: ### Token Authentication\n801: \n802: 1. If `auth_token` provided, use it\n803: 2. Else try read from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n804: 3. If token non-empty, set `Authorization: Bearer {token}` header\n\n(End of file - total 804 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-027 Design: AgentCube Python SDK — CodeInterpreterClient\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-027  \n**Module:** `sdk-python`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M (Medium)\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK provides a client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n\nThis implementation integrates with:\n- **Workload Manager API**: Control plane for session lifecycle management\n- **Router API**: Data plane for code execution and file operations\n- **Agent Runtime API**: For agent workload invocation\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/python-sdk/design.md","time":{"start":1775907961067,"end":1775907961083}}}}
