{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775907988234,"sessionID":"ses_283a356fcffemyg6eo3tM4HwaT","part":{"id":"prt_d7c5d5da1001pnQdccuV9l1806","messageID":"msg_d7c5d24970017edlzABssuwHMc","sessionID":"ses_283a356fcffemyg6eo3tM4HwaT","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 Design: AgentCube Python SDK — AgentRuntimeClient\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-028  \n6: **Module:** `sdk-python` / `agentcube`  \n7: **Language:** Python  \n8: **Size:** M (Medium)\n9: \n10: The AgentCube Python SDK provides Python client libraries (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n11: \n12: This design covers:\n13: - `CodeInterpreterClient` — High-level client for Code Interpreter session management\n14: - `AgentRuntimeClient` — High-level client for Agent Runtime invocation\n15: - Supporting data plane and control plane clients\n16: - Exception hierarchy and HTTP utilities\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## Architecture\n21: \n22: ### High-Level Design\n23: \n24: ```\n25: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n26: │                           AgentCube Python SDK                               │\n27: │                                                                              │\n28: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n29: │  │                      Public API Layer                                   │ │\n30: │  │  ┌─────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────┐                    │ │\n31: │  │  │ CodeInterpreterClient│    │ AgentRuntimeClient  │                    │ │\n32: │  │  │                     │    │                     │                    │ │\n33: │  │  │ • Session lifecycle │    │ • Invoke workloads  │                    │ │\n34: │  │  │ • Execute commands  │    │ • Bootstrap session │                    │ │\n35: │  │  │ • Manage files      │    │ • Context manager   │                    │ │\n36: │  │  └──────────┬──────────┘    └──────────┬──────────┘                    │ │\n37: │  └─────────────┼──────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────┘ │\n38: │                │                          │                                  │\n39: │                ▼                          ▼                                  │\n40: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n41: │  │                      Client Layer (Internal)                            │ │\n42: │  │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐ │ │\n43: │  │  │ ControlPlane     │  │ CodeInterpreterData    │  │ AgentRuntimeData │ │ │\n44: │  │  │ Client           │  │ PlaneClient            │  │ PlaneClient      │ │ │\n45: │  │  │                  │  │                        │  │                  │ │ │\n46: │  │  │ • create_session │  │ • execute_command      │  │ • bootstrap_     │ │ │\n47: │  │  │ • delete_session │  │ • write_file           │  │   session_id     │ │ │\n48: │  │  │                  │  │ • upload_file          │  │ • invoke         │ │ │\n49: │  │  └──────────────────┘  └────────────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘ │ │\n50: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n51: │                │                          │                                  │\n52: │                ▼                          ▼                                  │\n53: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n54: │  │                      HTTP Layer                                         │ │\n55: │  │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │ │\n56: │  │  │ requests.Session with HTTPAdapter (connection pooling)            │ │ │\n57: │  │  │                                                                   │ │ │\n58: │  │  │ • pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10                           │ │ │\n59: │  │  │ • timeout=(connect_timeout, read_timeout)                        │ │ │\n60: │  │  │ • Authorization: Bearer <token>                                  │ │ │\n61: │  │  │ • x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>                           │ │ │\n62: │  │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │ │\n63: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n64: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n65:                                     │\n66:                                     ▼\n67: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n68: │                           Backend Services                                   │\n69: │  ┌──────────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────┐  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n70: │  │ Workload Manager     │  │ Router               │  │ AgentRuntime      │  │\n71: │  │ (Control Plane)      │  │ (Data Plane)         │  │ Workloads         │  │\n72: │  └──────────────────────┘  └──────────────────────┘  └───────────────────┘  │\n73: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n74: ```\n75: \n76: ### Component Architecture\n77: \n78: ```\n79: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n80: │                      CodeInterpreterClient Flow                              │\n81: │                                                                              │\n82: │   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐ │\n83: │   │ __init__ │──►│ Create   │──►│ Init     │──►│ Execute  │──►│ Cleanup  │ │\n84: │   │          │   │ Session  │   │ Data     │   │ Commands │   │ on Exit  │ │\n85: │   │          │   │ (CP)     │   │ Plane    │   │ / Files  │   │          │ │\n86: │   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘ │\n87: │        │                                           │              │       │\n88: │        │                                           │              │       │\n89: │        │              ┌────────────────────────────┘              │       │\n90: │        │              │                                           │       │\n91: │        │              ▼                                           │       │\n92: │   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐ │\n93: │   │ Reuse    │   │ POST     │   │ POST     │   │ GET/POST │   │ DELETE   │ │\n94: │   │ session  │   │ /v1/code-│   │ api/exec │   │ api/files│   │ Session  │ │\n95: │   │ _id      │   │ interpreter│  │ ute      │   │          │   │ (CP)     │ │\n96: │   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘ │\n97: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n98: \n99: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n100: │                      AgentRuntimeClient Flow                                 │\n101: │                                                                              │\n102: │   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐ │\n103: │   │ __init__ │──►│ Bootstrap│──►│ POST     │──►│ Process  │──►│ Close    │ │\n104: │   │          │   │ Session  │   │ Invoke   │   │ Response │   │ Session  │ │\n105: │   │          │   │ ID (GET) │   │          │   │          │   │          │ │\n106: │   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘ │\n107: │        │                                           │              │       │\n108: │        │              Header: x-agentcube-session-id                    │       │\n109: │        │              Body: JSON payload                                │       │\n110: │        │                                           │              │       │\n111: │        ▼                                           ▼              ▼       │\n112: │   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐ │\n113: │   │ Validate │   │ GET      │   │ Header   │   │ Return   │   │ Close    │ │\n114: │   │ router_  │   │ /v1/names│   │ + JSON   │   │ JSON     │   │ requests │ │\n115: │   │ url      │   │ paces/...│   │ body     │   │ data     │   │ .Session │ │\n116: │   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘ │\n117: │                        /invocations/                                       │\n118: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n119: ```\n120: \n121: ### Component Interactions\n122: \n123: | Component | Purpose | Input | Output |\n124: |-----------|---------|-------|--------|\n125: | **CodeInterpreterClient** | High-level Code Interpreter interface | Config params, commands, code | Execution results, file handles |\n126: | **AgentRuntimeClient** | High-level Agent Runtime interface | Agent name, payload | Invocation response |\n127: | **ControlPlaneClient** | Workload Manager API client | Session parameters | Session ID |\n128: | **CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient** | Router API for Code Interpreter | Commands, files | Results, file data |\n129: | **AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient** | Router API for Agent Runtime | Session ID, payload | HTTP response |\n130: | **create_session** | HTTP session factory | Pool settings | Configured Session |\n131: \n132: ---\n133: \n134: ## Directory Structure\n135: \n136: ```\n137: agentcube/\n138: ├── __init__.py                      # Public exports (~30 lines)\n139: ├── code_interpreter.py              # CodeInterpreterClient (~320 lines)\n140: ├── agent_runtime.py                 # AgentRuntimeClient (~130 lines)\n141: ├── exceptions.py                    # Exception classes (~60 lines)\n142: ├── clients/\n143: │   ├── __init__.py                  # Re-exports (~15 lines)\n144: │   ├── control_plane.py             # ControlPlaneClient (~155 lines)\n145: │   ├── code_interpreter_data_plane.py   # CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient (~265 lines)\n146: │   └── agent_runtime_data_plane.py      # AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (~130 lines)\n147: └── utils/\n148:     ├── __init__.py                  # Module marker\n149:     ├── http.py                      # create_session, read_token_from_file (~65 lines)\n150:     └── log.py                       # get_logger (~30 lines)\n151: \n152: pyproject.toml                       # Package configuration\n153: ```\n154: \n155: ---\n156: \n157: ## Data Structures\n158: \n159: ### Domain Types\n160: \n161: #### CodeInterpreterClient\n162: \n163: ```python\n164: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n165:     \"\"\"High-level client for Code Interpreter session management and execution.\n166: \n167:     Attributes:\n168:         name: Session name (default: \"my-interpreter\").\n169:         namespace: Kubernetes namespace (default: \"default\").\n170:         ttl: Session TTL in seconds (default: 3600).\n171:         verbose: Enable verbose logging.\n172:         logger: Logger instance.\n173:         cp_client: Control plane client.\n174:         router_url: Router URL.\n175:         session_id: Session ID (created or provided).\n176:         dp_client: Data plane client.\n177:     \"\"\"\n178: \n179:     def __init__(\n180:         self,\n181:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n182:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n183:         ttl: int = 3600,\n184:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n185:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n186:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n187:         verbose: bool = False,\n188:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n189:     ): ...\n190: ```\n191: \n192: #### AgentRuntimeClient\n193: \n194: ```python\n195: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n196:     \"\"\"High-level client for Agent Runtime invocation.\n197: \n198:     Attributes:\n199:         agent_name: Name of the agent to invoke.\n200:         namespace: Kubernetes namespace (default: \"default\").\n201:         timeout: Read timeout in seconds (default: 120).\n202:         connect_timeout: Connect timeout in seconds (default: 5.0).\n203:         logger: Logger instance.\n204:         router_url: Router URL.\n205:         session_id: Session ID (bootstrapped or provided).\n206:         dp_client: Data plane client.\n207:     \"\"\"\n208: \n209:     def __init__(\n210:         self,\n211:         agent_name: str,\n212:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n213:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n214:         verbose: bool = False,\n215:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n216:         timeout: int = 120,\n217:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n218:     ): ...\n219: ```\n220: \n221: #### ControlPlaneClient\n222: \n223: ```python\n224: class ControlPlaneClient:\n225:     \"\"\"Client for Workload Manager control plane API.\n226: \n227:     Attributes:\n228:         base_url: The Workload Manager base URL.\n229:         timeout: Read timeout in seconds.\n230:         connect_timeout: Connect timeout in seconds.\n231:         session: The HTTP session with connection pooling.\n232:     \"\"\"\n233: \n234:     def __init__(\n235:         self,\n236:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n237:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n238:         timeout: int = 120,\n239:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n240:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n241:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n242:     ): ...\n243: ```\n244: \n245: #### CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n246: \n247: ```python\n248: class CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n249:     \"\"\"Client for Code Interpreter data plane operations.\n250: \n251:     Attributes:\n252:         session_id: The session ID for header injection.\n253:         base_url: The data plane base URL.\n254:         timeout: Read timeout in seconds.\n255:         connect_timeout: Connect timeout in seconds.\n256:         session: The HTTP session with connection pooling.\n257:     \"\"\"\n258: \n259:     def __init__(\n260:         self,\n261:         session_id: str,\n262:         base_url: str,\n263:         timeout: int = 120,\n264:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n265:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n266:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n267:     ): ...\n268: ```\n269: \n270: #### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n271: \n272: ```python\n273: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n274:     \"\"\"Client for Agent Runtime data plane operations.\n275: \n276:     Attributes:\n277:         base_url: The data plane base URL.\n278:         timeout: Read timeout in seconds.\n279:         connect_timeout: Connect timeout in seconds.\n280:         session: The HTTP session with connection pooling.\n281:     \"\"\"\n282: \n283:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n284: \n285:     def __init__(\n286:         self,\n287:         base_url: str,\n288:         timeout: int = 120,\n289:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n290:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n291:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n292:     ): ...\n293: ```\n294: \n295: ### Request/Response Types\n296: \n297: #### Code Interpreter Session Creation Request\n298: \n299: ```python\n300: # POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter\n301: {\n302:     \"name\": str,          # Session name\n303:     \"namespace\": str,     # Kubernetes namespace\n304:     \"ttl\": int,           # TTL in seconds\n305:     \"metadata\": dict,     # Optional metadata\n306: }\n307: \n308: # Response\n309: {\n310:     \"sessionId\": str,     # Unique session identifier\n311: }\n312: ```\n313: \n314: #### Code Interpreter Execute Request\n315: \n316: ```python\n317: # POST api/execute\n318: {\n319:     \"command\": List[str],     # Command as list of strings\n320:     \"timeout\": str,           # Timeout string (e.g., \"60s\")\n321: }\n322: \n323: # Response\n324: {\n325:     \"stdout\": str,\n326:     \"stderr\": str,\n327:     \"exit_code\": int,\n328: }\n329: ```\n330: \n331: #### Code Interpreter Files Request\n332: \n333: ```python\n334: # POST api/files (JSON)\n335: {\n336:     \"path\": str,          # Remote file path\n337:     \"content\": str,       # Base64-encoded content\n338:     \"mode\": str,          # File permissions (e.g., \"0644\")\n339: }\n340: \n341: # POST api/files (Multipart)\n342: # Form data:\n343: #   - file: binary content\n344: #   - path: remote path\n345: #   - mode: permissions\n346: \n347: # GET api/files/{clean_path}\n348: # Returns: File content as binary\n349: \n350: # GET api/files?path={path}\n351: # Returns: List[Dict[str, Any]] file listings\n352: ```\n353: \n354: #### Agent Runtime Invoke Request\n355: \n356: ```python\n357: # GET {base_url}\n358: # Response headers:\n359: #   x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>\n360: \n361: # POST {base_url}\n362: # Headers:\n363: #   x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>\n364: #   Content-Type: application/json\n365: # Body: Dict[str, Any] (payload)\n366: # Response: JSON data\n367: ```\n368: \n369: ### Internal Types\n370: \n371: #### HTTP Session Configuration\n372: \n373: ```python\n374: from requests.adapters import HTTPAdapter\n375: \n376: class SessionConfig:\n377:     \"\"\"Configuration for HTTP session.\"\"\"\n378:     pool_connections: int = 10\n379:     pool_maxsize: int = 10\n380:     timeout: int = 120\n381:     connect_timeout: float = 5.0\n382: ```\n383: \n384: ### Constants\n385: \n386: ```python\n387: # Default configuration values\n388: DEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 120\n389: DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT = 5.0\n390: DEFAULT_POOL_CONNECTIONS = 10\n391: DEFAULT_POOL_MAXSIZE = 10\n392: DEFAULT_TTL = 3600\n393: DEFAULT_NAMESPACE = \"default\"\n394: \n395: # Session header name\n396: SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n397: \n398: # Service account token path\n399: SERVICE_ACCOUNT_TOKEN_PATH = \"/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\"\n400: \n401: # Environment variable names\n402: ENV_ROUTER_URL = \"ROUTER_URL\"\n403: ENV_WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL = \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"\n404: ```\n405: \n406: ---\n407: \n408: ## API Contracts\n409: \n410: ### CodeInterpreterClient Interface\n411: \n412: ```python\n413: class CodeInterpreterClientInterface(Protocol):\n414:     \"\"\"Interface for CodeInterpreterClient.\n415: \n416:     Provides lifecycle management for Code Interpreter sessions and\n417:     operations for executing commands and managing files.\n418:     \"\"\"\n419: \n420:     def execute_command(\n421:         self,\n422:         command: List[str],\n423:         timeout: Optional[int] = None,\n424:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n425:         \"\"\"Execute a command in the Code Interpreter.\n426: \n427:         Returns:\n428:             Dictionary with stdout, stderr, and exit_code.\n429: \n430:         Raises:\n431:             CommandExecutionError: If command returns non-zero exit code.\n432:         \"\"\"\n433: \n434:     def run_code(\n435:         self,\n436:         code: str,\n437:         language: str = \"python\",\n438:         timeout: Optional[int] = None,\n439:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n440:         \"\"\"Execute code in the Code Interpreter.\n441: \n442:         For Python: writes timestamped .py file and executes with python3.\n443:         \"\"\"\n444: \n445:     def write_file(self, path: str, content: str, mode: str = \"0644\") -> None:\n446:         \"\"\"Write a file to the Code Interpreter workspace.\"\"\"\n447: \n448:     def upload_file(\n449:         self,\n450:         path: str,\n451:         content: Union[str, bytes, os.PathLike],\n452:         mode: str = \"0644\",\n453:     ) -> None:\n454:         \"\"\"Upload a file via multipart/form-data.\"\"\"\n455: \n456:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str) -> bytes:\n457:         \"\"\"Download a file from the Code Interpreter workspace.\"\"\"\n458: \n459:     def list_files(self, path: str = \"/\") -> List[Dict[str, Any]]:\n460:         \"\"\"List files in the Code Interpreter workspace.\"\"\"\n461: \n462:     def stop(self) -> None:\n463:         \"\"\"Stop the client and clean up resources.\"\"\"\n464: ```\n465: \n466: ### AgentRuntimeClient Interface\n467: \n468: ```python\n469: class AgentRuntimeClientInterface(Protocol):\n470:     \"\"\"Interface for AgentRuntimeClient.\n471: \n472:     Provides interface for invoking Agent Runtime workloads through\n473:     the Router API with session management.\n474:     \"\"\"\n475: \n476:     def invoke(\n477:         self,\n478:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n479:         timeout: Optional[int] = None,\n480:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n481:         \"\"\"Invoke the Agent Runtime with a payload.\n482: \n483:         Args:\n484:             payload: JSON payload to send to the agent.\n485:             timeout: Optional timeout override in seconds.\n486: \n487:         Returns:\n488:             Response data as dictionary.\n489: \n490:         Raises:\n491:             ValueError: If session_id is not initialized.\n492:         \"\"\"\n493: \n494:     def close(self) -> None:\n495:         \"\"\"Close the client and release resources.\"\"\"\n496: ```\n497: \n498: ### ControlPlaneClient Interface\n499: \n500: ```python\n501: class ControlPlaneClientInterface(Protocol):\n502:     \"\"\"Interface for ControlPlaneClient.\n503: \n504:     Manages session lifecycle through the Workload Manager API.\n505:     \"\"\"\n506: \n507:     def create_session(\n508:         self,\n509:         name: str,\n510:         namespace: str,\n511:         metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n512:         ttl: int = 3600,\n513:     ) -> str:\n514:         \"\"\"Create a new Code Interpreter session.\n515: \n516:         Returns:\n517:             The session ID string.\n518: \n519:         Raises:\n520:             ValueError: If response missing sessionId.\n521:         \"\"\"\n522: \n523:     def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool:\n524:         \"\"\"Delete a Code Interpreter session.\n525: \n526:         Returns:\n527:             True if deletion succeeded or session not found (404).\n528:             False if deletion failed.\n529:         \"\"\"\n530: \n531:     def close(self) -> None:\n532:         \"\"\"Close the HTTP session.\"\"\"\n533: ```\n534: \n535: ### Data Plane Clients Interface\n536: \n537: ```python\n538: class CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClientInterface(Protocol):\n539:     \"\"\"Data plane client for Code Interpreter operations.\"\"\"\n540: \n541:     def execute_command(\n542:         self,\n543:         command: List[str],\n544:         timeout: Optional[int] = None,\n545:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n546: \n547:     def write_file(\n548:         self,\n549:         path: str,\n550:         content: Union[str, bytes],\n551:         mode: str = \"0644\",\n552:     ) -> None: ...\n553: \n554:     def upload_file(\n555:         self,\n556:         path: str,\n557:         content: Union[str, bytes, os.PathLike],\n558:         mode: str = \"0644\",\n559:     ) -> None: ...\n560: \n561:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str) -> bytes: ...\n562: \n563:     def list_files(self, path: str = \"/\") -> List[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n564: \n565:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n566: \n567: \n568: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClientInterface(Protocol):\n569:     \"\"\"Data plane client for Agent Runtime operations.\"\"\"\n570: \n571:     SESSION_HEADER: str = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n572: \n573:     def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str:\n574:         \"\"\"Bootstrap session ID from invocation endpoint.\n575: \n576:         Returns:\n577:             Session ID from response header.\n578: \n579:         Raises:\n580:             ValueError: If session header missing.\n581:         \"\"\"\n582: \n583:     def invoke(\n584:         self,\n585:         session_id: str,\n586:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n587:         timeout: Optional[int] = None,\n588:     ) -> requests.Response:\n589:         \"\"\"Invoke Agent Runtime with payload.\n590: \n591:         Raises:\n592:             ValueError: If session_id is falsy.\n593:         \"\"\"\n594: \n595:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n596: ```\n597: \n598: ### HTTP Utilities\n599: \n600: ```python\n601: def create_session(\n602:     pool_connections: int = 10,\n603:     pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n604: ) -> requests.Session:\n605:     \"\"\"Create an HTTP session with connection pooling.\n606: \n607:     Mounts HTTPAdapter for http:// and https://.\n608:     \"\"\"\n609: \n610: def read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str:\n611:     \"\"\"Read authentication token from file.\n612: \n613:     Returns:\n614:         Token string stripped, or \"\" on FileNotFoundError.\n615:     \"\"\"\n616: \n617: def get_service_account_token() -> Optional[str]:\n618:     \"\"\"Read Kubernetes service account token.\n619: \n620:     Reads from /var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\n621:     \"\"\"\n622: ```\n623: \n624: ---\n625: \n626: ## Error Handling\n627: \n628: ### Error Categories and Codes\n629: \n630: | Error | Description | Retryable | Handling Strategy |\n631: |-------|-------------|-----------|-------------------|\n632: | `ValueError` | Missing required URL or session ID | No | Fail fast with clear message |\n633: | `CommandExecutionError` | Remote command non-zero exit | No | Raise with exit_code, stderr |\n634: | `requests.RequestException` | HTTP request failure | Varies | Re-raise for caller handling |\n635: | `SessionError` | Session management failure | Context | Available for extension |\n636: | `DataPlaneError` | Data plane operation failure | Context | Available for extension |\n637: \n638: ### Exception Hierarchy\n639: \n640: ```python\n641: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n642:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK.\"\"\"\n643:     pass\n644: \n645: \n646: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n647:     \"\"\"Raised when remote command returns non-zero exit code.\n648: \n649:     Attributes:\n650:         exit_code: The exit code returned.\n651:         stderr: Standard error output.\n652:         command: The executed command.\n653:     \"\"\"\n654: \n655:     def __init__(\n656:         self,\n657:         exit_code: int,\n658:         stderr: str,\n659:         command: Optional[str] = None,\n660:     ):\n661:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n662:         self.stderr = stderr\n663:         self.command = command\n664:         message = f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\"\n665:         if command:\n666:             message = f\"Command '{command}' failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\"\n667:         super().__init__(message)\n668: \n669: \n670: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n671:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails.\n672: \n673:     Defined for extension; core clients primarily use ValueError.\n674:     \"\"\"\n675:     pass\n676: \n677: \n678: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n679:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail.\n680: \n681:     Defined for extension; core clients use requests exceptions.\n682:     \"\"\"\n683:     pass\n684: ```\n685: \n686: ### Error Handling Patterns\n687: \n688: #### Router URL Validation\n689: \n690: ```python\n691: def __init__(self, ..., router_url: Optional[str] = None, ...):\n692:     self.router_url = router_url or os.environ.get(\"ROUTER_URL\")\n693:     if not self.router_url:\n694:         raise ValueError(\n695:             \"Router URL must be provided via argument or ROUTER_URL environment variable\"\n696:         )\n697: ```\n698: \n699: #### Session ID Validation\n700: \n701: ```python\n702: def invoke(self, session_id: str, ...):\n703:     if not session_id:\n704:         raise ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")\n705:     # ... proceed with invocation\n706: ```\n707: \n708: #### Command Execution Error\n709: \n710: ```python\n711: def execute_command(self, command: List[str], ...):\n712:     response = self._request(\"POST\", \"api/execute\", ...)\n713:     data = response.json()\n714:     exit_code = data.get(\"exit_code\", 0)\n715: \n716:     if exit_code != 0:\n717:         raise CommandExecutionError(\n718:             exit_code=exit_code,\n719:             stderr=data.get(\"stderr\", \"\"),\n720:             command=\" \".join(command),\n721:         )\n722:     return data\n723: ```\n724: \n725: #### Bootstrap Session Error\n726: \n727: ```python\n728: def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str:\n729:     response = self.session.get(self.base_url, ...)\n730:     response.raise_for_status()\n731: \n732:     session_id = response.headers.get(self.SESSION_HEADER)\n733:     if not session_id:\n734:         raise ValueError(f\"Missing required response header: {self.SESSION_HEADER}\")\n735:     return session_id\n736: ```\n737: \n738: #### Cleanup on Failure\n739: \n740: ```python\n741: def _create_and_init_session(self) -> None:\n742:     try:\n743:         self.session_id = self.cp_client.create_session(...)\n744:         self._init_data_plane()\n745:     except Exception:\n746:         # Clean up session if data plane init failed\n747:         if self.session_id and self._session_created_by_client:\n748:             self.cp_client.delete_session(self.session_id)\n749:             self.session_id = None\n750:         raise\n751: ```\n752: \n753: ---\n754: \n755: ## Testing Strategy\n756: \n757: ### Unit Tests\n758: \n759: #### test_code_interpreter_client.py\n760: \n761: ```python\n762: def test_code_interpreter_client_requires_router_url():\n763:     \"\"\"Router URL must be provided or set in environment.\"\"\"\n764:     with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Router URL must be provided\"):\n765:         CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=None)\n766:     # Ensure ROUTER_URL env is not set\n767:     old_env = os.environ.pop(\"ROUTER_URL\", None)\n768:     try:\n769:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Router URL must be provided\"):\n770:             CodeInterpreterClient()\n771:     finally:\n772:         if old_env:\n773:             os.environ[\"ROUTER_URL\"] = old_env\n774: \n775: \n776: def test_code_interpreter_client_reuses_session_id(mock_cp_client, mock_dp_client):\n777:     \"\"\"Client reuses provided session_id without creating new session.\"\"\"\n778:     with patch.object(\n779:         agentcube.code_interpreter, \"ControlPlaneClient\", return_value=mock_cp_client\n780:     ):\n781:         with patch.object(\n782:             agentcube.code_interpreter,\n783:             \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n784:             return_value=mock_dp_client,\n785:         ):\n786:             client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n787:                 router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n788:                 session_id=\"existing-session-123\",\n789:             )\n790:             assert client.session_id == \"existing-session-123\"\n791:             mock_cp_client.create_session.assert_not_called()\n792: \n793: \n794: def test_code_interpreter_client_cleanup_on_dp_init_failure(mock_cp_client):\n795:     \"\"\"Session is deleted if data plane init fails after creation.\"\"\"\n796:     mock_cp_client.create_session.return_value = \"new-session-456\"\n797: \n798:     with patch.object(\n799:         agentcube.code_interpreter, \"ControlPlaneClient\", return_value=mock_cp_client\n800:     ):\n801:         with patch.object(\n802:             agentcube.code_interpreter,\n803:             \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n804:             side_effect=Exception(\"Connection failed\"),\n805:         ):\n806:             with pytest.raises(Exception, match=\"Connection failed\"):\n807:                 CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://router:8080\")\n808: \n809:             # Session should be cleaned up\n810:             mock_cp_client.delete_session.assert_called_once_with(\"new-session-456\")\n811: \n812: \n813: def test_context_manager_calls_stop(mock_client):\n814:     \"\"\"Context manager calls stop() on exit.\"\"\"\n815:     with mock_client as client:\n816:         pass\n817:     mock_client.stop.assert_called_once()\n818: \n819: \n820: def test_execute_command_raises_on_non_zero_exit(mock_dp_client):\n821:     \"\"\"CommandExecutionError raised when exit_code != 0.\"\"\"\n822:     mock_dp_client.execute_command.return_value = {\n823:         \"stdout\": \"\",\n824:         \"stderr\": \"error message\",\n825:         \"exit_code\": 1,\n826:     }\n827:     # Test logic...\n828: ```\n829: \n830: #### test_agent_runtime_client.py\n831: \n832: ```python\n833: def test_agent_runtime_client_requires_router_url():\n834:     \"\"\"Router URL must be provided or set in environment.\"\"\"\n835:     with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Router URL must be provided\"):\n836:         AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=None)\n837: \n838: \n839: def test_agent_runtime_client_bootstrap_session_id(mock_dp_client):\n840:     \"\"\"Client bootstraps session_id when not provided.\"\"\"\n841:     mock_dp_client.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"bootstrapped-session\"\n842: \n843:     with patch.object(\n844:         agentcube.agent_runtime, \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\", return_value=mock_dp_client\n845:     ):\n846:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n847:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n848:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n849:         )\n850:         assert client.session_id == \"bootstrapped-session\"\n851: \n852: \n853: def test_agent_runtime_client_uses_provided_session_id(mock_dp_client):\n854:     \"\"\"Client uses provided session_id without bootstrapping.\"\"\"\n855:     mock_dp_client.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"bootstrapped-session\"\n856: \n857:     with patch.object(\n858:         agentcube.agent_runtime, \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\", return_value=mock_dp_client\n859:     ):\n860:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n861:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n862:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n863:             session_id=\"provided-session\",\n864:         )\n865:         assert client.session_id == \"provided-session\"\n866:         mock_dp_client.bootstrap_session_id.assert_not_called()\n867: \n868: \n869: def test_invoke_raises_without_session(mock_client):\n870:     \"\"\"ValueError raised when invoking without session_id.\"\"\"\n871:     mock_client.session_id = None\n872:     with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"session_id is not initialized\"):\n873:         mock_client.invoke({\"key\": \"value\"})\n874: \n875: \n876: def test_context_manager_calls_close(mock_client):\n877:     \"\"\"Context manager calls close() on exit.\"\"\"\n878:     with mock_client as client:\n879:         pass\n880:     mock_client.close.assert_called_once()\n881: ```\n882: \n883: #### test_control_plane_client.py\n884: \n885: ```python\n886: def test_create_session_returns_session_id(mock_session):\n887:     \"\"\"create_session returns sessionId from response.\"\"\"\n888:     mock_response = Mock()\n889:     mock_response.json.return_value = {\"sessionId\": \"session-123\"}\n890:     mock_session.post.return_value = mock_response\n891: \n892:     client = ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\")\n893:     client.session = mock_session\n894: \n895:     session_id = client.create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"default\")\n896:     assert session_id == \"session-123\"\n897: \n898: \n899: def test_create_session_raises_on_missing_session_id(mock_session):\n900:     \"\"\"ValueError raised when response missing sessionId.\"\"\"\n901:     mock_response = Mock()\n902:     mock_response.json.return_value = {}  # No sessionId\n903:     mock_session.post.return_value = mock_response\n904: \n905:     client = ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\")\n906:     client.session = mock_session\n907: \n908:     with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"sessionId\"):\n909:         client.create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"default\")\n910: \n911: \n912: def test_delete_session_returns_true_on_404(mock_session):\n913:     \"\"\"delete_session returns True on 404 (already deleted).\"\"\"\n914:     mock_response = Mock()\n915:     mock_response.status_code = 404\n916:     mock_session.delete.return_value = mock_response\n917: \n918:     client = ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\")\n919:     client.session = mock_session\n920: \n921:     result = client.delete_session(\"session-123\")\n922:     assert result is True\n923: ```\n924: \n925: #### test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py\n926: \n927: ```python\n928: def test_bootstrap_session_id_from_header(mock_session):\n929:     \"\"\"bootstrap_session_id extracts session ID from response header.\"\"\"\n930:     mock_response = Mock()\n931:     mock_response.headers = {\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"session-123\"}\n932:     mock_session.get.return_value = mock_response\n933: \n934:     client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://router:8080/invocations/\")\n935:     client.session = mock_session\n936: \n937:     session_id = client.bootstrap_session_id()\n938:     assert session_id == \"session-123\"\n939: \n940: \n941: def test_bootstrap_session_id_raises_on_missing_header(mock_session):\n942:     \"\"\"ValueError raised when session header missing.\"\"\"\n943:     mock_response = Mock()\n944:     mock_response.headers = {}  # No session header\n945:     mock_session.get.return_value = mock_response\n946: \n947:     client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://router:8080/invocations/\")\n948:     client.session = mock_session\n949: \n950:     with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"x-agentcube-session-id\"):\n951:         client.bootstrap_session_id()\n952: \n953: \n954: def test_invoke_sets_session_header(mock_session):\n955:     \"\"\"invoke sets x-agentcube-session-id header.\"\"\"\n956:     mock_response = Mock()\n957:     mock_session.post.return_value = mock_response\n958: \n959:     client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://router:8080/invocations/\")\n960:     client.session = mock_session\n961: \n962:     client.invoke(\n963:         session_id=\"session-123\",\n964:         payload={\"key\": \"value\"},\n965:     )\n966: \n967:     call_kwargs = mock_session.post.call_args[1]\n968:     headers = call_kwargs.get(\"headers\", {})\n969:     assert headers.get(\"x-agentcube-session-id\") == \"session-123\"\n970: \n971: \n972: def test_invoke_raises_on_empty_session_id():\n973:     \"\"\"ValueError raised when session_id is empty.\"\"\"\n974:     client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://router:8080/invocations/\")\n975: \n976:     with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"session_id\"):\n977:         client.invoke(session_id=\"\", payload={})\n978: ```\n979: \n980: ### Integration Tests\n981: \n982: ```python\n983: def test_code_interpreter_end_to_end():\n984:     \"\"\"Integration test for Code Interpreter flow.\"\"\"\n985:     if not os.environ.get(\"TEST_ROUTER_URL\"):\n986:         pytest.skip(\"TEST_ROUTER_URL not set\")\n987: \n988:     router_url = os.environ[\"TEST_ROUTER_URL\"]\n989:     workload_manager_url = os.environ.get(\"TEST_WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\")\n990: \n991:     with CodeInterpreterClient(\n992:         router_url=router_url,\n993:         workload_manager_url=workload_manager_url,\n994:     ) as client:\n995:         # Execute command\n996:         result = client.execute_command([\"echo\", \"hello\"])\n997:         assert result[\"exit_code\"] == 0\n998:         assert \"hello\" in result[\"stdout\"]\n999: \n1000:         # Write and read file\n1001:         client.write_file(\"/workspace/test.txt\", \"test content\")\n1002:         content = client.download_file(\"/workspace/test.txt\")\n1003:         assert content.decode() == \"test content\"\n1004: \n1005:         # List files\n1006:         files = client.list_files(\"/workspace\")\n1007:         assert any(f[\"name\"] == \"test.txt\" for f in files)\n1008: \n1009: \n1010: def test_agent_runtime_end_to_end():\n1011:     \"\"\"Integration test for Agent Runtime flow.\"\"\"\n1012:     if not os.environ.get(\"TEST_ROUTER_URL\"):\n1013:         pytest.skip(\"TEST_ROUTER_URL not set\")\n1014: \n1015:     router_url = os.environ[\"TEST_ROUTER_URL\"]\n1016:     agent_name = os.environ.get(\"TEST_AGENT_NAME\", \"test-agent\")\n1017: \n1018:     with AgentRuntimeClient(\n1019:         agent_name=agent_name,\n1020:         router_url=router_url,\n1021:     ) as client:\n1022:         response = client.invoke({\"input\": \"test\"})\n1023:         assert \"output\" in response\n1024: ```\n1025: \n1026: ### Test Execution\n1027: \n1028: ```bash\n1029: # Run all SDK tests\n1030: pytest tests/ -v\n1031: \n1032: # Run specific test modules\n1033: pytest tests/test_code_interpreter_client.py -v\n1034: pytest tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py -v\n1035: pytest tests/test_control_plane.py -v\n1036: \n1037: # Run with coverage\n1038: pytest tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=html\n1039: \n1040: # Run integration tests\n1041: pytest tests/ -m integration --env-file=.env.test\n1042: ```\n1043: \n1044: ---\n1045: \n1046: ## Security Considerations\n1047: \n1048: ### Authentication\n1049: \n1050: - **Service Account Token**: Automatically read from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n1051: - **Bearer Token**: Set as `Authorization: Bearer {token}` header on control plane requests\n1052: - **Router JWT**: Handled by Router; SDK does not set Authorization on data plane requests\n1053: \n1054: ### Session Header\n1055: \n1056: - **Session ID**: Passed via `x-agentcube-session-id` header on all data plane requests\n1057: - **Lowercase Header**: Consistent lowercase header name across all clients\n1058: \n1059: ### URL Validation\n1060: \n1061: ```python\n1062: # Router URL is required\n1063: if not self.router_url:\n1064:     raise ValueError(\"Router URL must be provided...\")\n1065: \n1066: # Workload Manager URL is required for control plane operations\n1067: if not self.base_url:\n1068:     raise ValueError(\"Workload Manager URL must be provided...\")\n1069: ```\n1070: \n1071: ### Timeout Safety\n1072: \n1073: ```python\n1074: # Read timeout buffer for command execution\n1075: # Avoids ReadTimeout before PicoD returns exit 124\n1076: read_timeout = effective_timeout + 2.0\n1077: ```\n1078: \n1079: ---\n1080: \n1081: ## Performance Considerations\n1082: \n1083: ### Connection Pooling\n1084: \n1085: | Setting | Default | Purpose |\n1086: |---------|---------|---------|\n1087: | pool_connections | 10 | Number of connection pools to cache |\n1088: | pool_maxsize | 10 | Maximum connections to save per pool |\n1089: | timeout | 120s | Default read timeout |\n1090: | connect_timeout | 5.0s | Connection establishment timeout |\n1091: \n1092: ### Timeout Behavior\n1093: \n1094: | Operation | Connect Timeout | Read Timeout |\n1095: |-----------|-----------------|--------------|\n1096: | Control plane | 5.0s | 120s |\n1097: | Data plane execute | 5.0s | timeout + 2.0s |\n1098: | Data plane invoke | 5.0s | 120s (configurable) |\n1099: | Bootstrap session | 5.0s | 120s |\n1100: \n1101: ### Resource Management\n1102: \n1103: - **Context Managers**: All clients support `with` statement for automatic cleanup\n1104: - **Session Reuse**: Single HTTP session per client with connection pooling\n1105: - **Explicit Close**: `close()` method for resource cleanup outside context managers\n1106: \n1107: ---\n1108: \n1109: ## Integration Points\n1110: \n1111: ### With Workload Manager (Control Plane)\n1112: \n1113: ```python\n1114: # Create session\n1115: POST {workload_manager_url}/v1/code-interpreter\n1116: # Body: {\"name\", \"namespace\", \"ttl\", \"metadata\"}\n1117: # Response: {\"sessionId\"}\n1118: \n1119: # Delete session\n1120: DELETE {workload_manager_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}\n1121: ```\n1122: \n1123: ### With Router (Data Plane - Code Interpreter)\n1124: \n1125: ```python\n1126: # Base URL construction\n1127: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{name}/invocations/\"\n1128: base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n1129: \n1130: # Execute command\n1131: POST {base_url}/api/execute\n1132: # Body: {\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}\n1133: \n1134: # Write file\n1135: POST {base_url}/api/files\n1136: # Body: {\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\"}\n1137: \n1138: # Upload file\n1139: POST {base_url}/api/files (multipart)\n1140: # Form: files={'file': ...}, data={'path', 'mode'}\n1141: \n1142: # Download file\n1143: GET {base_url}/api/files/{clean_path}\n1144: # Response: File content (stream=True)\n1145: \n1146: # List files\n1147: GET {base_url}/api/files?path={path}\n1148: # Response: List of file info\n1149: ```\n1150: \n1151: ### With Router (Data Plane - Agent Runtime)\n1152: \n1153: ```python\n1154: # Base URL construction\n1155: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n1156: base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n1157: \n1158: # Bootstrap session\n1159: GET {base_url}\n1160: # Response header: x-agentcube-session-id\n1161: \n1162: # Invoke\n1163: POST {base_url}\n1164: # Headers: x-agentcube-session-id, Content-Type: application/json\n1165: # Body: JSON payload\n1166: # Response: JSON data\n1167: ```\n1168: \n1169: ---\n1170: \n1171: ## Dependencies\n1172: \n1173: ```toml\n1174: # pyproject.toml\n1175: [project]\n1176: name = \"agentcube-cli\"\n1177: requires-python = \">=3.9\"\n1178: \n1179: dependencies = [\n1180:     \"requests>=2.31.0\",\n1181:     # ... other dependencies\n1182: ]\n1183: \n1184: [project.optional-dependencies]\n1185: dev = [\n1186:     \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n1187:     \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n1188:     # ...\n1189: ]\n1190: ```\n1191: \n1192: | Package | Purpose | Version |\n1193: |---------|---------|---------|\n1194: | `requests` | HTTP client with session pooling | >=2.31.0 |\n1195: | `pytest` | Testing framework | >=7.4.0 (dev) |\n1196: | `pytest-cov` | Coverage reporting | >=4.1.0 (dev) |\n1197: \n1198: ---\n1199: \n1200: ## References\n1201: \n1202: - [AgentCube Python SDK Specification](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/.sdd_prompt.md) — Detailed SDK specification\n1203: - [Code Interpreter Client](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/code_interpreter.py) — CodeInterpreterClient implementation\n1204: - [Agent Runtime Client](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/agent_runtime.py) — AgentRuntimeClient implementation\n1205: - [Control Plane Client](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py) — ControlPlaneClient implementation\n1206: - [Code Interpreter Data Plane](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py) — CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient implementation\n1207: - [Agent Runtime Data Plane](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py) — AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient implementation\n1208: - [Exceptions](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/exceptions.py) — Exception hierarchy\n1209: - [HTTP Utilities](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/utils/http.py) — HTTP session factory\n1210: \n1211: ---\n1212: \n1213: *AR-028 — Module: sdk-python — Language: Python — Size: M*\n\n(End of file - total 1213 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 Design: AgentCube Python SDK — AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-028  \n**Module:** `sdk-python` / `agentcube`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M (Medium)\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK provides Python client libraries (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n\nThis design covers:\n- `CodeInterpreterClient` — High-level client for Code Interpreter session management\n- `AgentRuntimeClient` — High-level client for Agent Runtime invocation\n- Supporting data plane and control plane clients\n- Exception hierarchy and HTTP utilities\n\n---\n\n## Architecture","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/design.md","time":{"start":1775907988214,"end":1775907988228}}}}
