{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775908225067,"sessionID":"ses_283a356fcffemyg6eo3tM4HwaT","part":{"id":"prt_d7c5da267001wYILYDhcbpF151","messageID":"msg_d7c5d6343001ogAowozoVDlP1F","sessionID":"ses_283a356fcffemyg6eo3tM4HwaT","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/python-sdk/design.md","content":"# AR-029 Design: AgentCube Python SDK — HTTP Underlying Client\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-029  \n**Module:** `sdk-python`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M (Medium)\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK HTTP underlying client provides the foundational HTTP layer for all SDK operations. This module implements connection pooling, session management, timeout handling, authentication, and retry mechanisms that support both the Control Plane (Workload Manager) and Data Plane (Router) communications.\n\nThis design covers:\n- HTTP session factory with connection pooling\n- Authentication and token management\n- Timeout configuration and handling\n- Session header management\n- HTTP utilities and helpers\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### HTTP Layer Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         AgentCube Python SDK                                   │\n│                                                                              │\n│  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│  │                      Public API Layer                                   │ │\n│  │  ┌─────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────┐                   │ │\n│  │  │ CodeInterpreterClient│    │ AgentRuntimeClient  │                   │ │\n│  │  └──────────┬──────────┘    └──────────┬──────────┘                   │ │\n│  └─────────────┼──────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────┘ │\n│                │                          │                                  │\n│                ▼                          ▼                                  │\n│  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│  │                      Client Layer                                       │ │\n│  │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐ │ │\n│  │  │ ControlPlane     │  │ CodeInterpreterData    │  │ AgentRuntimeData│ │ │\n│  │  │ Client           │  │ PlaneClient            │  │ PlaneClient     │ │ │\n│  │  └──────────┬───────┘  └───────────┬────────────┘  └────────┬────────┘ │ │\n│  └─────────────┼──────────────────────┼────────────────────────┼──────────┘ │\n│                │                      │                        │            │\n│                ▼                      ▼                        ▼            │\n│  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│  │                      HTTP Underlying Client Layer (AR-029)              │ │\n│  │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │ │\n│  │  │ create_session() — HTTP Session Factory                           │ │ │\n│  │  │ ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │ │ │\n│  │  │ │ HTTPAdapter (Connection Pooling)                            │   │ │ │\n│  │  │ │ • pool_connections=10 (cache pools)                         │   │ │ │\n│  │  │ │ • pool_maxsize=10 (max per pool)                            │   │ │ │\n│  │  │ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │ │ │\n│  │  │ ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │ │ │\n│  │  │ │ Timeout Configuration                                       │   │ │ │\n│  │  │ │ • connect_timeout=5.0s                                      │   │ │ │\n│  │  │ │ • read_timeout=120s                                         │   │ │ │\n│  │  │ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │ │ │\n│  │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │ │\n│  │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │ │\n│  │  │ Authentication & Token Management                                 │ │ │\n│  │  │ ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │ │ │\n│  │  │ │ read_token_from_file()                                      │   │ │ │\n│  │  │ │ • Service account token: /var/run/secrets/.../token         │   │ │ │\n│  │  │ │ • Returns: token string or \"\" on FileNotFoundError          │   │ │ │\n│  │  │ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │ │ │\n│  │  │ ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │ │ │\n│  │  │ │ Authorization Header                                        │   │ │ │\n│  │  │ │ • Control Plane: Bearer <token>                             │   │ │ │\n│  │  │ │ • Data Plane: Router handles JWT (no SDK auth)              │   │ │ │\n│  │  │ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │ │ │\n│  │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │ │\n│  │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │ │\n│  │  │ Session Header Management                                         │ │ │\n│  │  │ • Header: x-agentcube-session-id (lowercase)                      │ │ │\n│  │  │ • Default on data plane sessions                                  │ │ │\n│  │  │ • Explicit on multipart uploads                                   │ │ │\n│  │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │ │\n│  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                                     │\n                                     ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                           Backend Services                                   │\n│  ┌──────────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────┐  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n│  │ Workload Manager     │  │ Router               │  │ AgentRuntime      │  │\n│  │ (Control Plane)      │  │ (Data Plane)         │  │ Workloads         │  │\n│  └──────────────────────┘  └──────────────────────┘  └───────────────────┘  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### HTTP Client Flow\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      HTTP Session Creation Flow                               │\n│                                                                              │\n│   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐ │\n│   │ Client   │──▶│ create_  │──▶│ Create   │──▶│ Mount    │──▶│ Return   │ │\n│   │ Requests │   │ session  │   │ requests │   │ HTTP     │   │ Configured│ │\n│   │ Session  │   │ ()       │   │ .Session│   │ Adapter  │   │ Session  │ │\n│   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘ │\n│        │                                              │             │      │\n│        │                                              │             │      │\n│        │              ┌───────────────────────────────┘             │      │\n│        │              │                                             │      │\n│        │              ▼                                             │      │\n│   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐ │\n│   │ Session  │◀──│ Use for  │◀──│ Apply    │◀──│ Set      │◀──│ Configure│ │\n│   │ Pooling  │   │ Requests │   │ Headers  │   │ Timeouts │   │ Pool     │ │\n│   │ Enabled  │   │          │   │ (Auth)   │   │          │   │ Settings │ │\n│   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘ │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Authentication Flow\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      Token Resolution Flow                                    │\n│                                                                              │\n│   ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐│\n│   │ ControlPlaneClient.__init__(auth_token=None)                           ││\n│   └───────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘│\n│                                   │                                         │\n│                                   ▼                                         │\n│   ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐│\n│   │ Token Resolution                                                       ││\n│   │ ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐    ││\n│   │ │ auth_token  │─▶│  If None,   │─▶│read_token_ │─▶│   Return    │    ││\n│   │ │  arg given? │  │  read from  │  │from_file() │  │   token or  │    ││\n│   │ └─────────────┘  │  SA file    │  └─────────────┘  │     \"\"      │    ││\n│   └──────────────────┴─────────────┴───────────────────┴─────────────┘    ││\n│                                   │                                         │\n│                                   ▼                                         │\n│   ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐│\n│   │ Header Setup                                                           ││\n│   │ if token:                                                               ││\n│   │   session.headers[\"Authorization\"] = f\"Bearer {token}\"                 ││\n│   └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘│\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Directory Structure\n\n```\nsdk-python/\n├── pyproject.toml                          # Package configuration\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── __init__.py                         # Public exports\n│   ├── code_interpreter.py                 # CodeInterpreterClient\n│   ├── agent_runtime.py                    # AgentRuntimeClient\n│   ├── exceptions.py                       # Exception hierarchy\n│   ├── clients/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                     # Client re-exports\n│   │   ├── control_plane.py                # ControlPlaneClient (HTTP client)\n│   │   ├── code_interpreter_data_plane.py  # CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n│   │   └── agent_runtime_data_plane.py     # AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n│   └── utils/\n│       ├── __init__.py                     # Module marker\n│       ├── http.py                         # create_session, HTTP utilities\n│       ├── utils.py                        # read_token_from_file\n│       └── log.py                          # get_logger\n├── examples/\n│   ├── basic_usage.py                      # CodeInterpreter example\n│   └── agent_runtime_usage.py              # AgentRuntime example\n├── scripts/\n│   └── e2e_picod_test.py                   # End-to-end test\n└── tests/\n    ├── test_utils_http.py                  # HTTP utility tests\n    ├── test_control_plane.py               # Control plane tests\n    └── test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py # Data plane tests\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### HTTP Session Configuration\n\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass HTTPSessionConfig:\n    \"\"\"Configuration for HTTP session with connection pooling.\n    \n    Attributes:\n        pool_connections: Number of connection pools to cache.\n        pool_maxsize: Maximum number of connections to save per pool.\n        timeout: Read timeout in seconds.\n        connect_timeout: Connection establishment timeout in seconds.\n    \"\"\"\n    pool_connections: int = 10\n    pool_maxsize: int = 10\n    timeout: int = 120\n    connect_timeout: float = 5.0\n```\n\n### Timeout Tuple Structure\n\n```python\n# Used by requests.Session.request() timeout parameter\nTimeoutTuple = Tuple[float, float]  # (connect_timeout, read_timeout)\n\n# Example usage:\ntimeout: TimeoutTuple = (5.0, 120)  # 5s connect, 120s read\n```\n\n### HTTP Header Constants\n\n```python\n# Session header name (lowercase as per spec)\nSESSION_HEADER: str = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n\n# Content type headers\nCONTENT_TYPE_JSON: str = \"application/json\"\nCONTENT_TYPE_MULTIPART: str = \"multipart/form-data\"\n\n# Authorization header prefix\nAUTH_BEARER_PREFIX: str = \"Bearer\"\n```\n\n### Service Account Token Path\n\n```python\n# Kubernetes service account token path\nSERVICE_ACCOUNT_TOKEN_PATH: str = \"/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\"\n```\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n```python\n# Environment variable names\nENV_ROUTER_URL: str = \"ROUTER_URL\"\nENV_WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL: str = \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### create_session\n\n```python\ndef create_session(\n    pool_connections: int = 10,\n    pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n) -> requests.Session:\n    \"\"\"Create an HTTP session with connection pooling.\n\n    Creates a requests.Session with HTTPAdapter mounted for both\n    http:// and https:// protocols to enable connection pooling.\n\n    Args:\n        pool_connections: Number of connection pools to cache.\n        pool_maxsize: Maximum number of connections to save per pool.\n\n    Returns:\n        Configured requests.Session with connection pooling enabled.\n\n    Example:\n        >>> session = create_session(pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10)\n        >>> response = session.get(\"https://example.com/api\")\n        >>> session.close()\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Implementation Details:**\n\n```python\ndef create_session(\n    pool_connections: int = 10,\n    pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n) -> requests.Session:\n    session = requests.Session()\n    adapter = HTTPAdapter(\n        pool_connections=pool_connections,\n        pool_maxsize=pool_maxsize,\n    )\n    session.mount(\"http://\", adapter)\n    session.mount(\"https://\", adapter)\n    return session\n```\n\n### read_token_from_file\n\n```python\ndef read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Read authentication token from file.\n\n    Reads the contents of a file and returns it stripped of whitespace.\n    Used primarily for reading Kubernetes service account tokens.\n\n    Args:\n        file_path: Path to the token file.\n\n    Returns:\n        Token string stripped of whitespace, or empty string if file\n        not found.\n\n    Example:\n        >>> token = read_token_from_file(\n        ...     \"/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\"\n        ... )\n        >>> if token:\n        ...     headers[\"Authorization\"] = f\"Bearer {token}\"\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Implementation Details:**\n\n```python\ndef read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str:\n    try:\n        with open(file_path, \"r\") as f:\n            return f.read().strip()\n    except FileNotFoundError:\n        return \"\"\n```\n\n### ControlPlaneClient HTTP Contract\n\n```python\nclass ControlPlaneClient:\n    \"\"\"Control plane client with HTTP session management.\n\n    HTTP Configuration:\n        - base_url: Resolved from workload_manager_url arg or WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env\n        - timeout: 120 seconds (read timeout)\n        - connect_timeout: 5.0 seconds\n        - pool_connections: 10\n        - pool_maxsize: 10\n        - Authorization: Bearer {token} (if token non-empty)\n\n    Endpoints:\n        POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter\n        DELETE {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ):\n        \"\"\"Initialize control plane client with HTTP session.\n\n        Args:\n            workload_manager_url: Base URL for Workload Manager.\n            auth_token: Bearer token for authorization.\n            timeout: Read timeout in seconds.\n            connect_timeout: Connect timeout in seconds.\n            pool_connections: Connection pool size.\n            pool_maxsize: Max connections per pool.\n        \"\"\"\n```\n\n**HTTP Headers (Default on session):**\n\n```python\n# Content-Type set on all requests\nsession.headers[\"Content-Type\"] = \"application/json\"\n\n# Authorization set if token is non-empty\nif token:\n    session.headers[\"Authorization\"] = f\"Bearer {token}\"\n```\n\n**Timeout Tuple:**\n\n```python\n# Used for each request: (connect_timeout, timeout)\ntimeout_tuple: Tuple[float, int] = (connect_timeout, timeout)\n\n# Example request:\nresponse = session.post(\n    url,\n    json=data,\n    timeout=(connect_timeout, timeout),\n)\n```\n\n### CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient HTTP Contract\n\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n    \"\"\"Data plane client for Code Interpreter with HTTP session.\n\n    HTTP Configuration:\n        - timeout: 120 seconds (read timeout)\n        - connect_timeout: 5.0 seconds\n        - pool_connections: 10\n        - pool_maxsize: 10\n        - Default header: x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}\n\n    Base URL Construction:\n        If base_url not provided:\n            base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\n            base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n\n    Endpoints (relative to base_url):\n        POST api/execute — Execute command\n        POST api/files — Write file (JSON) or upload (multipart)\n        GET api/files/{clean_path} — Download file\n        GET api/files?path={path} — List files\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        session_id: str,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n        cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n        base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ):\n        \"\"\"Initialize data plane client with HTTP session.\n\n        Args:\n            session_id: Session ID for header injection.\n            router_url: Router base URL.\n            namespace: Kubernetes namespace.\n            cr_name: Code interpreter CR name.\n            base_url: Optional explicit base URL (overrides construction).\n            timeout: Read timeout in seconds.\n            connect_timeout: Connect timeout in seconds.\n            pool_connections: Connection pool size.\n            pool_maxsize: Max connections per pool.\n        \"\"\"\n```\n\n**HTTP Request Patterns:**\n\n```python\n# Default headers on session\nsession.headers[SESSION_HEADER] = session_id\n\n# JSON POST (e.g., execute_command)\nresponse = session.post(\n    f\"{base_url}api/execute\",\n    json={\"command\": command, \"timeout\": f\"{timeout}s\"},\n    timeout=(connect_timeout, read_timeout),\n)\n\n# Multipart POST (e.g., upload_file)\n# Note: No JSON Content-Type on outer request\nresponse = session.post(\n    f\"{base_url}api/files\",\n    files={\"file\": file_content},\n    data={\"path\": path, \"mode\": mode},\n    headers={SESSION_HEADER: session_id},  # Explicit for multipart\n)\n\n# GET with streaming (e.g., download_file)\nresponse = session.get(\n    f\"{base_url}api/files/{clean_path}\",\n    stream=True,\n    timeout=(connect_timeout, timeout),\n)\n```\n\n**Timeout Buffer Pattern:**\n\n```python\n# For execute_command: add 2.0s buffer to avoid ReadTimeout\n# before PicoD returns exit 124\nread_timeout = timeout_value + 2.0\nresponse = session.post(\n    f\"{base_url}api/execute\",\n    json={\"command\": command, \"timeout\": f\"{timeout_value}s\"},\n    timeout=(connect_timeout, read_timeout),\n)\n```\n\n### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient HTTP Contract\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n    \"\"\"Data plane client for Agent Runtime with HTTP session.\n\n    HTTP Configuration:\n        - timeout: 120 seconds (read timeout)\n        - connect_timeout: 5.0 seconds\n        - pool_connections: 10\n        - pool_maxsize: 10\n        - SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n\n    Base URL Construction:\n        base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n        base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n\n    Endpoints:\n        GET {base_url} — Bootstrap session ID\n        POST {base_url} — Invoke agent with payload\n    \"\"\"\n\n    SESSION_HEADER: str = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        router_url: str,\n        namespace: str,\n        agent_name: str,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ):\n        \"\"\"Initialize agent runtime data plane client.\n\n        Args:\n            router_url: Router base URL.\n            namespace: Kubernetes namespace.\n            agent_name: Name of the agent.\n            timeout: Read timeout in seconds.\n            connect_timeout: Connect timeout in seconds.\n            pool_connections: Connection pool size.\n            pool_maxsize: Max connections per pool.\n        \"\"\"\n```\n\n**HTTP Request Patterns:**\n\n```python\n# Bootstrap session ID (GET)\nresponse = session.get(\n    base_url,\n    timeout=(connect_timeout, timeout),\n)\nsession_id = response.headers.get(SESSION_HEADER)\nif not session_id:\n    raise ValueError(f\"Missing required response header: {SESSION_HEADER}\")\n\n# Invoke (POST)\nresponse = session.post(\n    base_url,\n    json=payload,\n    headers={SESSION_HEADER: session_id, \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"},\n    timeout=(connect_timeout, timeout),\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### HTTP Error Scenarios\n\n| Scenario | Error Type | HTTP Detail |\n|----------|------------|-------------|\n| Connection timeout | `requests.ConnectTimeout` | Connection establishment exceeded connect_timeout |\n| Read timeout | `requests.ReadTimeout` | Response not received within read timeout |\n| HTTP error status | `requests.HTTPError` | Response has 4xx/5xx status code |\n| Connection error | `requests.ConnectionError` | DNS failure, refused connection, etc. |\n| Missing session header | `ValueError` | `x-agentcube-session-id` not in response headers |\n| Invalid URL | `ValueError` | Router URL or Workload Manager URL not provided |\n\n### Timeout Handling\n\n```python\n# Default timeouts\nDEFAULT_TIMEOUT: int = 120          # seconds\nDEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT: float = 5.0  # seconds\n\n# Timeout tuple for requests\ntimeout: Tuple[float, int] = (connect_timeout, read_timeout)\n\n# Special case: execute_command timeout buffer\ndef _get_execute_timeout(effective_timeout: float) -> Tuple[float, float]:\n    \"\"\"Get timeout tuple with buffer for execute commands.\n    \n    Adds 2.0s buffer to avoid ReadTimeout before PicoD returns exit 124.\n    \"\"\"\n    return (connect_timeout, effective_timeout + 2.0)\n```\n\n### Response Validation\n\n```python\n# Raise HTTPError for 4xx/5xx status codes\nresponse.raise_for_status()\n\n# Check for session ID in response headers\nsession_id = response.headers.get(\"x-agentcube-session-id\")\nif not session_id:\n    raise ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")\n\n# Validate JSON response has expected fields\ndata = response.json()\nsession_id = data.get(\"sessionId\")\nif not session_id:\n    raise ValueError(\"Response missing sessionId\")\n```\n\n---\n\n## Configuration Resolution\n\n### No Centralized Configuration Class\n\nThe SDK uses distributed configuration resolution:\n\n| Component | Setting | Resolution Order |\n|-----------|---------|------------------|\n| `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` | `workload_manager_url` arg → `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env |\n| `ControlPlaneClient` | `auth_token` | `auth_token` arg → `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` file |\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` | `router_url` arg → `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n| `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` | `router_url` arg → `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n\n### Default HTTP Settings\n\n| Setting | Value | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| timeout | 120 | Read timeout in seconds |\n| connect_timeout | 5.0 | Connect timeout in seconds |\n| pool_connections | 10 | Connection pools to cache |\n| pool_maxsize | 10 | Max connections per pool |\n\n### Configuration Code Examples\n\n```python\n# ControlPlaneClient URL resolution\ndef _resolve_base_url(self, workload_manager_url: Optional[str]) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Resolve Workload Manager base URL.\"\"\"\n    url = workload_manager_url or os.environ.get(\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\")\n    if not url:\n        raise ValueError(\n            \"Workload Manager URL must be provided via argument or \"\n            \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL environment variable\"\n        )\n    return url.rstrip(\"/\")\n\n# ControlPlaneClient token resolution\ndef _resolve_auth_token(self, auth_token: Optional[str]) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Resolve authentication token.\"\"\"\n    if auth_token:\n        return auth_token\n    return read_token_from_file(SERVICE_ACCOUNT_TOKEN_PATH)\n\n# CodeInterpreterClient router URL resolution\ndef _resolve_router_url(self, router_url: Optional[str]) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Resolve Router URL.\"\"\"\n    url = router_url or os.environ.get(\"ROUTER_URL\")\n    if not url:\n        raise ValueError(\n            \"Router URL must be provided via argument or \"\n            \"ROUTER_URL environment variable\"\n        )\n    return url.rstrip(\"/\")\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests for HTTP Layer\n\n#### test_utils_http.py\n\n```python\nclass TestCreateSession:\n    \"\"\"Tests for create_session HTTP factory.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_create_session_returns_requests_session(self):\n        \"\"\"create_session returns a configured requests.Session.\"\"\"\n        session = create_session()\n        \n        assert isinstance(session, requests.Session)\n        # Check adapters are mounted\n        assert \"https://\" in session.adapters\n        assert \"http://\" in session.adapters\n\n    def test_create_session_configures_pool_settings(self):\n        \"\"\"HTTPAdapter is configured with pool settings.\"\"\"\n        session = create_session(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=30)\n        \n        adapter = session.get_adapter(\"https://example.com\")\n        assert isinstance(adapter, HTTPAdapter)\n        # Pool settings are configured on the adapter\n\n    def test_create_session_default_pool_settings(self):\n        \"\"\"Default pool settings are 10/10.\"\"\"\n        session = create_session()\n        \n        adapter = session.get_adapter(\"https://example.com\")\n        # Verify default pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10\n\n\nclass TestReadTokenFromFile:\n    \"\"\"Tests for read_token_from_file utility.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_read_token_returns_stripped_content(self, tmp_path):\n        \"\"\"Token file content is returned stripped.\"\"\"\n        token_file = tmp_path / \"token\"\n        token_file.write_text(\"my-token\\n  \")\n        \n        token = read_token_from_file(str(token_file))\n        \n        assert token == \"my-token\"\n\n    def test_read_token_empty_file_returns_empty_string(self, tmp_path):\n        \"\"\"Empty file returns empty string.\"\"\"\n        token_file = tmp_path / \"token\"\n        token_file.write_text(\"\")\n        \n        token = read_token_from_file(str(token_file))\n        \n        assert token == \"\"\n\n    def test_read_token_missing_file_returns_empty_string(self, tmp_path):\n        \"\"\"Missing file returns empty string, not exception.\"\"\"\n        token = read_token_from_file(str(tmp_path / \"nonexistent\"))\n        \n        assert token == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestControlPlaneHTTP:\n    \"\"\"Tests for ControlPlaneClient HTTP behavior.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_session_has_content_type_header(self):\n        \"\"\"Session has Content-Type: application/json header.\"\"\"\n        client = ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\")\n        \n        assert client.session.headers.get(\"Content-Type\") == \"application/json\"\n\n    def test_session_has_authorization_with_token(self):\n        \"\"\"Authorization header set when token provided.\"\"\"\n        client = ControlPlaneClient(\n            workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\",\n            auth_token=\"my-token\",\n        )\n        \n        assert client.session.headers.get(\"Authorization\") == \"Bearer my-token\"\n\n    def test_session_no_authorization_without_token(self):\n        \"\"\"No Authorization header when token is empty.\"\"\"\n        client = ControlPlaneClient(\n            workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\",\n            auth_token=\"\",\n        )\n        \n        assert \"Authorization\" not in client.session.headers\n\n    @patch(\"agentcube.utils.http.read_token_from_file\")\n    def test_session_uses_service_account_token(self, mock_read_token):\n        \"\"\"Service account token used when auth_token not provided.\"\"\"\n        mock_read_token.return_value = \"sa-token\"\n        \n        client = ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\")\n        \n        mock_read_token.assert_called_once_with(\n            \"/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\"\n        )\n        assert client.session.headers.get(\"Authorization\") == \"Bearer sa-token\"\n\n    def test_create_session_uses_timeout_tuple(self, mock_session):\n        \"\"\"create_session uses (connect_timeout, timeout) tuple.\"\"\"\n        client = ControlPlaneClient(\n            workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\",\n            timeout=60,\n            connect_timeout=3.0,\n        )\n        client.session = mock_session\n        \n        client.create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"default\")\n        \n        call_kwargs = mock_session.post.call_args[1]\n        assert call_kwargs[\"timeout\"] == (3.0, 60)\n\n\nclass TestCodeInterpreterDataPlaneHTTP:\n    \"\"\"Tests for CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient HTTP behavior.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_session_has_session_header(self):\n        \"\"\"Session has x-agentcube-session-id header.\"\"\"\n        client = CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(\n            session_id=\"test-session\",\n            base_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n        )\n        \n        assert client.session.headers.get(\"x-agentcube-session-id\") == \"test-session\"\n\n    def test_base_url_construction_from_parts(self):\n        \"\"\"Base URL constructed from router_url, namespace, cr_name.\"\"\"\n        client = CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(\n            session_id=\"test\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            namespace=\"my-ns\",\n            cr_name=\"my-ci\",\n        )\n        \n        expected_path = \"/v1/namespaces/my-ns/code-interpreters/my-ci/invocations/\"\n        assert client.base_url.endswith(expected_path)\n\n    def test_explicit_base_url_overrides_construction(self):\n        \"\"\"Explicit base_url overrides constructed URL.\"\"\"\n        client = CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(\n            session_id=\"test\",\n            base_url=\"http://custom:8080/api/\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n        )\n        \n        assert client.base_url == \"http://custom:8080/api/\"\n\n    def test_execute_command_timeout_buffer(self, mock_session):\n        \"\"\"execute_command adds 2.0s buffer to read timeout.\"\"\"\n        client = CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(\n            session_id=\"test\",\n            base_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            timeout=120,\n            connect_timeout=5.0,\n        )\n        client.session = mock_session\n        \n        client.execute_command([\"echo\", \"hi\"], timeout=60)\n        \n        call_kwargs = mock_session.post.call_args[1]\n        # timeout should be (connect, read + 2.0) = (5.0, 62.0)\n        assert call_kwargs[\"timeout\"] == (5.0, 62.0)\n\n\nclass TestAgentRuntimeDataPlaneHTTP:\n    \"\"\"Tests for AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient HTTP behavior.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_bootstrap_extracts_session_header(self, mock_session):\n        \"\"\"bootstrap_session_id extracts header from GET response.\"\"\"\n        mock_response = Mock()\n        mock_response.headers = {\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"session-123\"}\n        mock_session.get.return_value = mock_response\n        \n        client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n        )\n        client.session = mock_session\n        \n        session_id = client.bootstrap_session_id()\n        \n        assert session_id == \"session-123\"\n\n    def test_bootstrap_raises_on_missing_header(self, mock_session):\n        \"\"\"bootstrap_session_id raises ValueError if header missing.\"\"\"\n        mock_response = Mock()\n        mock_response.headers = {}  # No session header\n        mock_session.get.return_value = mock_response\n        \n        client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n        )\n        client.session = mock_session\n        \n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"x-agentcube-session-id\"):\n            client.bootstrap_session_id()\n\n    def test_invoke_sets_session_header(self, mock_session):\n        \"\"\"invoke includes x-agentcube-session-id in headers.\"\"\"\n        mock_session.post.return_value = Mock()\n        \n        client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n        )\n        client.session = mock_session\n        \n        client.invoke(session_id=\"session-123\", payload={\"key\": \"value\"})\n        \n        call_kwargs = mock_session.post.call_args[1]\n        headers = call_kwargs.get(\"headers\", {})\n        assert headers.get(\"x-agentcube-session-id\") == \"session-123\"\n        assert headers.get(\"Content-Type\") == \"application/json\"\n\n    def test_invoke_raises_on_empty_session_id(self):\n        \"\"\"invoke raises ValueError when session_id is empty.\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n        )\n        \n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"session_id is not initialized\"):\n            client.invoke(session_id=\"\", payload={})\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n```python\nclass TestHTTPIntegration:\n    \"\"\"Integration tests for HTTP layer.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_connection_pooling_reuses_connections(self):\n        \"\"\"Multiple requests reuse connections from pool.\"\"\"\n        # This would require a real or mock server to verify\n        pass\n\n    def test_timeout_actually_times_out(self):\n        \"\"\"Verify timeout parameters are respected.\"\"\"\n        # Test with a slow-responding endpoint\n        pass\n\n    def test_session_header_persistence(self):\n        \"\"\"Session header persists across multiple requests.\"\"\"\n        pass\n```\n\n---\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### Authentication Patterns\n\n```python\n# Control Plane: Bearer token authentication\ndef _setup_auth_headers(self, token: str) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Setup authorization headers if token is non-empty.\"\"\"\n    if token:\n        self.session.headers[\"Authorization\"] = f\"Bearer {token}\"\n\n# Data Plane: No SDK-side JWT (handled by Router)\n# Note: Router handles JWT validation; SDK only passes session header\n```\n\n### Token Security\n\n```python\n# Token is read from secure location\ndef _get_service_account_token() -> Optional[str]:\n    \"\"\"Read token from Kubernetes service account file.\"\"\"\n    token_path = \"/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\"\n    try:\n        with open(token_path, \"r\") as f:\n            return f.read().strip()\n    except (FileNotFoundError, PermissionError):\n        return None\n```\n\n### Session Header Security\n\n```python\n# Session ID is passed via header on all data plane requests\nSESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n\n# Header is set as default on session (lowercase as per HTTP/2 requirements)\nsession.headers[SESSION_HEADER] = session_id\n```\n\n---\n\n## Performance Considerations\n\n### Connection Pooling Benefits\n\n| Metric | Without Pooling | With Pooling |\n|--------|----------------|--------------|\n| Connection establishment | Per request | Once per destination |\n| TCP handshake overhead | High | Minimized |\n| Memory usage | Lower | Slightly higher |\n| Latency (subsequent requests) | Higher | Lower |\n\n### Timeout Tuning\n\n```python\n# Connect timeout should be short (network issues fail fast)\nCONNECT_TIMEOUT = 5.0  # seconds\n\n# Read timeout should accommodate long-running operations\nREAD_TIMEOUT = 120  # seconds\n\n# Execute timeout buffer prevents race conditions\nEXECUTE_TIMEOUT_BUFFER = 2.0  # seconds\n```\n\n### Resource Cleanup\n\n```python\n# Always close sessions to release connections\ndef close(self) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Close HTTP session and release resources.\"\"\"\n    if self.session:\n        self.session.close()\n\n# Context manager ensures cleanup\nwith CodeInterpreterClient(...) as client:\n    # Use client\n    pass  # Session automatically closed\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n```toml\n# pyproject.toml\n[project]\nname = \"agentcube-sdk\"\nrequires-python = \">=3.10\"\n\ndependencies = [\n    \"requests>=2.31.0\",\n    \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n    \"cryptography>=41.0.0\",\n]\n```\n\n| Package | Purpose | Version |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `requests` | HTTP client with session pooling | >=2.31.0 |\n| `PyJWT` | JWT token handling | >=2.0.0 |\n| `cryptography` | Cryptographic operations | >=41.0.0 |\n\n---\n\n## Integration Points\n\n### With requests Library\n\n```python\n# Session factory wraps requests.Session\nimport requests\nfrom requests.adapters import HTTPAdapter\n\ndef create_session(...) -> requests.Session:\n    session = requests.Session()\n    adapter = HTTPAdapter(pool_connections=..., pool_maxsize=...)\n    session.mount(\"http://\", adapter)\n    session.mount(\"https://\", adapter)\n    return session\n```\n\n### With Control Plane Client\n\n```python\n# ControlPlaneClient uses create_session\nclass ControlPlaneClient:\n    def __init__(self, ...):\n        self.session = create_session(\n            pool_connections=pool_connections,\n            pool_maxsize=pool_maxsize,\n        )\n        # Configure headers, timeouts\n```\n\n### With Data Plane Clients\n\n```python\n# Data plane clients use create_session with session header\nclass CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n    def __init__(self, session_id: str, ...):\n        self.session = create_session(...)\n        self.session.headers[\"x-agentcube-session-id\"] = session_id\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [AgentCube Python SDK Specification](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/.sdd_prompt.md) — Detailed SDK specification\n- [AR-027 Design](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/python-sdk/design.md) — CodeInterpreterClient design\n- [AR-028 Design](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/design.md) — AgentRuntimeClient design\n- [HTTP Adapter Documentation](https://requests.readthedocs.io/en/latest/user/advanced/#id1) — requests HTTPAdapter\n- [Connection Pooling](https://requests.readthedocs.io/en/latest/user/advanced/#keep-alive) — requests keep-alive\n\n---\n\n*AR-029 — Module: sdk-python — Language: Python — Size: M*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/python-sdk/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/python-sdk/design.md","time":{"start":1775908224754,"end":1775908225063}}}}
