{"type":"text","timestamp":1775908271124,"sessionID":"ses_283a356fcffemyg6eo3tM4HwaT","part":{"id":"prt_d7c617faf001TcALFL5tNkLTzR","messageID":"msg_d7c610068001ld0tbqTIaWTnY0","sessionID":"ses_283a356fcffemyg6eo3tM4HwaT","type":"text","text":"I've created the `design.md` file for AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端 in `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/python-sdk/design.md`.\n\nThe document includes comprehensive technical implementation details:\n\n## Summary of Contents\n\n**Architecture**\n- HTTP Layer Architecture diagram showing the relationship between public API, client layer, and HTTP underlying client layer\n- HTTP Session Creation Flow\n- Token Resolution Flow\n\n**Data Structures**\n- `HTTPSessionConfig` dataclass for HTTP configuration\n- Timeout tuple structure\n- HTTP header constants (`x-agentcube-session-id`, Content-Type, Authorization)\n- Service account token path and environment variables\n\n**API Contracts**\n- `create_session()` - HTTP session factory with connection pooling\n- `read_token_from_file()` - Token reader utility\n- `ControlPlaneClient` HTTP contract with headers and timeout tuple\n- `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` HTTP patterns including multipart uploads\n- `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` HTTP patterns including session bootstrap\n\n**Error Handling**\n- HTTP error scenarios and handling strategies\n- Timeout configuration with 2.0s buffer for execute commands\n- Response validation patterns\n\n**Configuration Resolution**\n- Distributed configuration (no centralized class)\n- Default HTTP settings (timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0, pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10)\n\n**Testing Strategy**\n- Unit tests for HTTP utilities\n- Tests for authentication patterns\n- Integration test patterns\n\n**Security & Performance**\n- Bearer token authentication pattern\n- Connection pooling benefits\n- Resource cleanup via context managers\n\nThe design aligns with the existing AR-027 and AR-028 designs and provides the HTTP layer foundation that both higher-level clients depend on.","time":{"start":1775908271122,"end":1775908271122}}}
